title: damson-caramel pie
directions: Set aside egg whites and mix remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in with other mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer the chicken, peas and carrots in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the chicken broth, cream of celery soup and the cream of chicken soup.
Pour over the meat and vegetables.
In the blender, mix the butter, milk, self-rising flour and baking powder.
Pour over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: german venison steak
directions: Combine catsup, water, onion, sugar and pepper in saucepan. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine beef broth granules, cracker crumbs and onion flakes.
Beat eggs.
Dip steaks in eggs.
Roll in cracker crumb mixture.
Place in skillet and brown on both sides. Remove to baking dish.
Cover with sauce and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly with a whisk.
Add sugar or honey, salt and vanilla.
Add cold milk and whisk until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into individual custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Place in
pan 2 to 2 1/2 inches deep.
Pour boiling water around the cups so that the water comes about to the level of the custard.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 50 minutes or until a stainless steel knife comes out clean when inserted in the center.
Remove from water and let cool. Chill and serve plain in cups.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; gradually beat in Eagle Brand and ReaLime.
Stir in food coloring. Pour into pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Peel and slice any good, hard apples into even slices.
Granny Smith apples are a good example.
Spread apple slices on a cloth and let dry for 3 to 4 days, in the sun if possible.
They will look like leather when dry.
Be sure to take them in at night and don't let the dew fall on them!

title: gale's famous brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with an electric mixer until a thick batter forms.
Spread batter evenly in the prepared pan and bake for 25 minutes.
These are great topped with a scoop of ice cream!

title: turkey vegetable skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown turkey, onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until the turkey is cooked and zucchini is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven chicken fricassee
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Coat with flour mixture.
Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Pour mixture over chicken; cover baking dish with foil.
Continue baking until chicken is tender (about 40 minutes).
Remove foil the last 10 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: jennie's golden potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt, and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with a little milk and shake a few at a time in bag, coating well.
Melt butter in 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch pan.
Layer potatoes.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour, turning once.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, milk, Crisco, vanilla, brown sugar and egg.
Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Drop heaping spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet that's ungreased.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: "to die for" fudge
directions: Place the sugar, cocoa, cream, and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan and heat over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Continue cooking until it reaches 234° on candy thermometer or a drop forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and stir in butter, until well mixed. Add vanilla and nuts, if desired, while stirring. Pour the fudge onto buttered 9 x 9 inch pan. When cooled and hardened, cut into squares.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet or can be rolled out for cut-out cookies.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Melt chocolate squares in double boiler or small bowl in microwave. Set aside to cool.
Cream butter until creamy and light.
Slowly beat in sugar for about 7 minutes until fluffy.
Add eggs slowly with vanilla; mix well.
Add chocolate.
Mix well.
In separate bowl sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture 1/3 at a time, mixing well.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried green beans
directions: Drain 2 cans; add all of 2 cans of beans.
Add Crisco.	Put in an iron skillet and cook until all liquid is gone.
Let brown to extent you want them.

title: pepper bread
directions: Heat shortening in skillet; mix all other ingredients.
After shortening has melted, pour into mixture.
Return all mixture into skillet.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring first 8 ingredients to boil.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Lower heat to low; cover and simmer 45 minutes. May add ham or other vegetables.

title: french beef slice
directions: Cut the French bread lengthwise and carefully scoop out the inside. (Break the scooped out bread into bite size pieces and save for later.)
In a large pan, cook the ground chuck until brown, adding onions towards the end so they don't burn. Pour off any excess liquid.
Stir in soups and bread pieces.
Spoon meat mixture into bottom half of bread shell and cover with top half. Wrap in foil, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into slices to serve 8 to 10.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and press out excess water. Combine all the ingredients and stir well. Chill for several hour before serving.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Open pina colada mix, combine with water in a large punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice and mix well.
Place in freezer overnight.
Take out of freezer one hour before serving.
Add ginger ale and pineapple slices before serving.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese and oleo together.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Cream well.

title: oven-fried lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in shallow pan in oven. Flour chicken and roll in butter.
Place, skin side down, in pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn. Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken and bake 30 minutes longer.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes after turning. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: baked round steak
directions: Place steak on foil and sprinkle with soup mix.
Place potatoes evenly over steak and pour mushrooms over steak and potatoes.
Wrap foil tight; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian stuffed yellow squash
directions: Cook squash until almost done, then cut in half lengthwise, scoop out pulp and set aside.
Cook sausage, onion and green pepper over medium-high heat until browned.
Drain well.
Stir together tomato, cheese, meat mixture and spoon into salted squash shells.
Place squash into a shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
(Spices may be added to your taste.)

title: dream drops
directions: Cook pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar in small, heavy pan, uncovered, until thick, stirring often. Cook 20 minutes or more. Cream shortening and sugar; add flavorings and beaten eggs.
Stir the soda into the pineapple and add to creamed mixture with half the sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in dates and nuts and then the remaining dry ingredients.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased and lightly floured baking sheet.
Bake at 350°
for about 12 minutes.

title: jalapeno stuffing and cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use to stuff jalapenos, spread on crackers, make sandwiches, etc.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, mayo, lemon juice and water together (first layer of casserole).
Lay chicken on top.
Spread layer of cheese, broccoli and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot spiced fruit compote
directions: Combine fruits in nonmetallic bowl or container.
Divide between glass casserole dishes (usually 2-quart casseroles are best).
Add brown sugar with spices in a large 4-cup measure; add Port wine to sugar mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over the fruit in each casserole.
Stir fruit carefully, being careful not to disturb or bruise the fruit.
Place in preheated 350° oven; cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be eaten hot or cold; it is great served warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: crunchy tossed salad
directions: In a jar with a tight fitting lid, mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Shake well until well blended. Chill for about an hour (do not chill overnight).

title: company salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir in broccoli.
Crush chips on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Sauce:
Stir soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Cook chicken and broccoli until tender (not together).
Place chicken and broccoli in large casserole dish. Cover with sauce, then top with cheese.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Can bake in 3 layers.

title: mounds bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut over crust.
Pour can of milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Spread hot chocolate with a spoon.
Refrigerate, cut and serve.

title: apple-honey oatmeal muffins
directions: Generously butter a 12-cup muffin tin.
Mix first six ingredients well in a medium bowl.
In a small bowl, blend egg and milk with applesauce, honey and butter.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix with fork just until moistened.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Cook corn and broccoli separately 1/2 cooking time.
Drain. Melt margarine; mix with Cheez Whiz.
Add cheese mixture to vegetables.
Add croutons.
Place in well-greased casserole dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients and make into patties or rolls. Roll in water, then roll in cornmeal. Fry in oil.

title: mud
directions: First, bake cake, make pudding and smash all 6 candy bars into tiny pieces.
In the bottom of a large bowl, put 1/3 of the cake, cut in cubes, layered.
Now, put 1/3 of the pudding and then 1/3 of the Cool Whip.
Last, put 2 of the smashed candy bars on top of each layer of Cool Whip.
Make 3 sets of layers of cake, pudding and Cool Whip.
For an extra kick, put gummy worms in the top layer of Cool Whip.

title: delicious pickled peaches
directions: Tie spices in cloth bag.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices in a large saucepan.
Add as many peaches as syrup will cover.
Cover and cook until peaches are tender.
Remove peaches from syrup; pack in sterilized jars. Boil syrup until thick.
Pour over peaches.
Seal jars.

title: lemon pudding for 2 with blueberry sauce
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 1 minute.
Add milk, lemon rind, lemon juice and butter; beat well.
Add flour; beat well until blended. Pour mixture between 2 custard cups sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Place custard cups in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Add water to the pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until set.
Remove cups from water and set aside.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut out and bake at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese squares
directions: Take 1 package crescent rolls.
Roll out to form a rectangle and fit into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over dough.
Take other package of rolls and roll out as before.
Fit on top of cream cheese.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Cream the shortening with the sugar and spices. Add the eggs and beat well. Then add alternately the coffee and the flour which has been sifted with the baking powder. Lastly add the raisins and the nuts. Bake a tester to see if the amount of flour is right, before dropping the rest of the dough by small teaspoonfuls onto oiled baking sheets.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender; drain off most of water. Coat bread crumbs with butter.
Combine all ingredients together. Place in casserole dish; bake at 350°.
Save some crumbs for top.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding. Fold in Cool Whip. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on the tortilla.
Roll up tortilla.
Place in a Ziploc bag and refrigerate, at least 2 days.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices and serve with salsa.

title: italian casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with oil.
Arrange potatoes and peppers in bottom of dish.
Combine the seasonings. Sprinkle 1/3 of the seasonings over potatoes.
Layer chicken and sausage over potatoes and seasonings.
Sprinkle remaining seasonings on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° for 35 minutes, then serve.

title: leche flan
directions: Scald the milk. Beat egg yolks with sugar, milk and lemon rind. Pour into mold lined with caramelized sugar. Place mold in pan half-filled with water and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is firm. Then place in the broiler section of the oven to brown top, about 5 to 6 minutes. Unmold from container to a serving dish. Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave vanilla pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar in 4-cup glass measure.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Microwave, uncovered, on full power 3 minutes. Stir.
Microwave again on full power 2 to 8 minutes or until boiling and thickened, stirring each minute to keep smooth.
Pour pudding into individual serving dishes when thick enough to form a ribbon.

title: crab and pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done, but firm.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add onion, celery, crab meat, salt and pepper.
Add 6 hard boiled eggs - diced.
Mix lightly.
Add ranch dressing and mayonnaise and fold in lightly.
Top with remaining eggs - cut horizontally.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs.
Add 1 cup cooking oil and mix well, then add flour and seasonings until smooth.
Fold in tart apples and nuts.
Blend well.
Beat oven to 375°.
Pour cake mix into a tube pan and bake for approximately 45 minutes.
Cover with a light icing of confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla flavor.

title: mix ahead meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover cookie sheets with waxed paper. Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Chill until easy to handle. Roll into 1-inch balls, with Skittle in center, if desired.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.
If any stick, release by dampening waxed paper on opposite side.

title: chocolate delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Brown flour, melted margarine and pecans 15 minutes at 375°.

title: dumpy cake
directions: Mix fruit and cake mix.
Pour into baking pan and pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together, except chips and 1/2 of cheese.
Put in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese and crushed chips and bake 15 minutes at 450° with foil covering or lid.
Remove cover and brown.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 3 eggs and softened cream cheese and pour over crust mix.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients until thick and creamy.

title: country style pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce and simmer for 3 or more hours.
If you have leftover ham, this may be added towards last.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Place steamer insert into wok.
Pour water into wok.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, milk, cinnamon and vanilla extract.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture into the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole dish.
Add 1/3 of the bread and raisins. Press down until bread absorbs some liquid.
Continue to layer ingredients, ending with milk mixture.
Press down until bread absorbs most of the liquid.
Place casserole dish on steamer. Cover top of dish with waxed paper.
Cover wok.
Set heat dial at 250° or cook over medium flame.
Steam.
Check water level after 30 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Don't let the wok cook dry. Steam for an hour or until a knife inserted 1-inch from the center comes out dry.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Put cheese and milk in pan.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
When cheese is melted, add butter and flour.
Mix well.
Ready to serve when thickened.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Saute ground beef and drain on paper towel.
Grease large skillet.
Heat grease. Pour half of batter into skillet.
Sprinkle cheese and meat.
Add onion and peppers and pour rest of batter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with pinto beans.

title: cauliflower pasta
directions: In a large pot, saute garlic in oil. Do not let it brown. Pour in water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Toss in cauliflower flowerets and pasta. Cook al dente.
Add parsley and cheese. Allow to sit 1 minute before serving.
Stir well to mix melted cheese throughout pasta.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs
until light
and
foamy.
Add
sugar,
oil, zucchini and vanilla, mixing lightly but well.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking
powder and cinnamon; add to zucchini-egg
mixture.
Stir
until
well	blended.
Add
nuts and raisins.
Pour in two well-greased and	floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.	Bake in 350° oven
for	60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on racks before slicing.

title: chicken
directions: Mix dressing, jam and soup mix together.
Place chicken in large shallow baking pan.
Pour mixture over chicken; bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: delicious winter jam
directions: Soak apricots overnight, covered with water.
Next day, cook until well done.
When well done, put through sieve.
Add pineapple; boil several minutes, then add sugar and lemon juice. Cook until desired thickness, about a half hour.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients with mayonnaise to mix easily.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and juice from oranges together for 2 minutes. Add oranges and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely before icing.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nutmeg.
Place in casserole dish. Start in cold oven.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Add nutmeg.

title: meatballs with water chestnuts
directions: Soak the bread cubes in milk and squeeze out as much milk as possible.
Add bread to the beef and sausage or pork.
These may be made with all beef.
Season with onion powder, garlic salt, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Add water chestnuts to the meat and mix thoroughly.
Shape into about 4 dozen small balls.
Brown in hot shortening or salad oil in chafing dish or skillet.

title: crunchies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil (important).
Boil oleo and sugar 2 1/2 minutes.
Put crackers in pan on foil.
Sprinkle nuts over crackers and pour oleo/sugar over crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil at once.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy, in large bowl.
Mix on lowest speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately top with candy kiss and press down until cookie cracks.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Drop onto cookie sheets by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove from oven.
Press 1/2 marshmallow on top of each and bake 2 minutes longer.
Frost when cool.

title: biscuits(sweet milk)
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together; work in shortening and add milk.
Stir together to make soft ball.
Put flour on bread board and form dough into flat ball.
Roll out with rolling pin about 1-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter. Grease baking sheet and put biscuits on close to each other. Makes 2 dozen.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for about 15 minutes.
Put lard pieces on top before baking in indention on biscuit.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Place 5 large onions into buttered casserole dish.
Layer crackers, sausage and last onion.
Mix soup with milk and pour on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until onions are cooked.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and add spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 2 - 3 hrs.
The longer the better.
Cook and drain lasagna noodles. Grease 13 x 9 pan and layer with noodles.
Spoon part of beef mixture on top.
Layer with mozzarella cheese; cottage cheese mixture.
Continue layering as above and end with beef mixture. Grate fresh parmesan on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until hot and bubbly, usually 25 - 30 minutes.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into 2 cups milk.
Let come to a boil, making a mush.
Add remainder of milk, well-beaten eggs, salt, sugar, baking powder and melted butter.
Bake in a casserole dish in a moderate oven to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls the first 4 ingredients.
Melt and blend well chocolate chips and wax.
Dip ball with toothpick into chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on low until blended; then mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, drizzle a mixture of confectioners sugar and lemon juice over top.
(Mixture should be thick but runny).

title: caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and syrup.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Mixture will foam.
Pour mixture over popcorn in a large roaster.
Stir until coated.
Place pan in 200° oven; stir every 5 minutes until popcorn dries.
Remove from oven.
Stir to separate popcorn.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix turkey with all ingredients; sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch by 13-inch pan and bake for 30-45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all. Enjoy with crackers and/or special little breads.

title: joyce's barbecue kolbassi
directions: Mix and cook in crock-pot for at least 2 hours, stirring often.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together and pour into a baking dish. Sprinkle with a mixture of 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake in a moderate oven (about 325°) about 30 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into freezer.
Fill the rest of the way up with milk or chocolate milk.

title: prizewinning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, mix thoroughly but lightly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nachos grande
directions: Cook ground beef with onions.
Drain fat off.
Season meat. Spread beans in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Top with meat; cover with cheese.
Drizzle salsa over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add alternately with milk; beat well.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mocked catfish
directions: Cook cornmeal in boiling salted water until done.
Take off stove.
Gradually add hominy and salmon.
Mix all together and make into loaf and roll in wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Slice off and roll in cornmeal and fry.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Grind the oranges and raisins.
Cook rhubarb.
Mix the cooked rhubarb, ground oranges and raisins.
Add sugar.
Cook until thick.
Pour into small jars and seal.

title: carrot cheddar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Store tightly covered.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, stir together sugar, milk and salt.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add butter; boil until it forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth; pour into pan.
Cut when cool.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces.
Brown steak in oil with onion, garlic, salt and pepper, beef cube and mushrooms.
Cook 25 minutes.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and soy sauce.
Cook again for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: peppermint-eggnog punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a punch bowl, stirring until blended.
Serve immediately with peppermint.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: eggplant spread
directions: Saute all ingredients on low-medium heat until cooked.
(Takes long time; couple hours or more.)
Will look like a lumpy sandwich spread, rather dark in color, sometimes almost black. Serve on crackers or appetizer sandwich bread.

title: stained glass fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough dressing or mayonnaise to taste.
Add salt and pepper.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O.
Add hot water.
Mix well. Bring to a boil; stirring with a whisk until very thick and smooth.
Set
aside to cool.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour
cooled
mixture
over strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip on pie.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise; remove yolks and mash well. Combine egg yolks with mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, pepper, paprika and dry mustard. Mix well. Refill egg whites. After filling, dust with paprika.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cheese rings
directions: Grate cheese.
Let margarine come to room temperature.
Mix well by hand.
Run through cookie press with the star disc.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together.
Place in crust.
Refrigerate 3-4 hours before serving.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Mix in milk, shortening and vanilla with fork until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter. Bake 40 minutes or until done. Cool.
Good with ice cream.

title: sausage supper
directions: In frypan, brown first three ingredients.
Drain excess fat. Add all other ingredients except cream cheese.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes stirring frequently.
Stir in softened cream cheese. Do not boil.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; add eggs and cake coloring.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Use Confectioners Sugar Icing or Marshmallow Icing as desired.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate the cheese in food processor.
When it is grated, cut the margarine on top of the cheese.
Add the flour to which the salt and pepper have been added.
Process the mixture until it forms a ball.
Remove from the processor and form a roll that will fit the cookie press.
Squirt onto a cookie sheet in rows.
Cook at 275°.
It takes about 40 minutes to bake. Cut the straws the length you want and put into container.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Put applesauce in large bowl and add soda, mixing well.
Sift flour and add cinnamon, allspice and salt; mix together.
Add sugar mixture to applesauce.
Add flour in last and mix well.
Pour in cake pans that have been greased well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan or 35 minutes in cake pans.
Remove to racks to cool.

title: b~b~q veggies
directions: Wrap all veggies in aluminum foil. Put butter, pepper, and salt on top and cook for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: cinna-sticks
directions: Pre-heat deep fryer to 450 degrees.
Slice tortillas into strips and deep fry until crispy golden brown.
Put cinnamon and sugar in plastic baggie and shake up to mix.
Put tortilla strips in baggie while still warm and shake well.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and keep refrigerated.
Use as dip for corn chips.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Spray the bottom and sides of a glass casserole dish with Pam. Spread thawed hash browns on bottom.
Stir in cream of chicken soup, sour cream, half of shredded cheese and chopped green onion. Combine all ingredients well.
Top with remaining cheese and green onions.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: low-fat pie pastry
directions: Mix the flour and salt.
Cut the oil into the flour with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle the milk over the flour; toss with a fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of the bowl.
Gather pastry into a ball; divide in half. Shape each half into flattened round ball on lightly-floured cloth-covered board of between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Roll the pastry 2 inches larger than inverted pie plate.
Fold the pastry into quarters; unfold and east into plate, pressing firmly against bottom and side.
Trim overhanging edge of pastry 1 inch from rim of plate. Fold and roll pastry under, even with plate; flute.
Fill and bake as directed.

title: strawberry nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add strawberry nectar. Cool, but not set. Add strawberries, bananas and Cool Whip. Blend well. Chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir together and pour into rectangle baking dish.

title: 24-hour twinkie delight
directions: Put banana slices on Twinkies, then top with crushed pineapple. Mix pudding according to package directions and pour on top of other layers.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Before serving, garnish with cherries.

title: peppy parmesan potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Cut potatoes with peelings into bite size pieces.
Place potatoes into prepared dish.
Add onions, pepper, salt and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: parmesan baked eggs
directions: Spray individual baking cups with nonstick spray. Sprinkle about a teaspoon of grated Parmesan evenly into cup. Break an egg into each cup. Add 1 teaspoon of half and half to each cup. Evenly sprinkle Parmesan onto each egg. Add a dash of paprika. Bake at 300° to 350° for about 15 minutes or until yolks are firm.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add flour and stir in.
Add 1 3/4 cups milk and cook until thick.
Turn heat off.
Add chips and chicken soup.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Put 4 slices of cheese on top and melt.

title: wedding pie
directions: Mix all well with happy years, children, grey hairs, troubles and prosperity.
Bake at medium temperature.
Serve with God's richest blessings on your fiftieth wedding anniversary.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables and continue cooking for 5 minutes; drain.
Set aside to cool for 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, Velveeta and bread cubes; place in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Beat milk and eggs together and pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cover and bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable-cheese bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli or cauliflower.
Place in baking dish. Pour remaining ingredients over vegetables.
Top with crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and set aside (fine).
Blend together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk and pudding together and then blend with cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Fold in 12 ounces Cool Whip.
In the flower pot, put in a layer of crushed cookies, then a layer of filling; alternate until top is finished with cookies.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Place artificial flower in center.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, garlic and paprika. Cook and stir over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in 1 cup water, bouillon granules and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken breasts.
Cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning meat once or twice.
Transfer chicken to platter.
Cover with foil and set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms.
Decap and scoop out inside of mushrooms.
Put filling (1/2 teaspoon) into each mushroom and put on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix last four ingredients together.
In casserole, layer chicken, half of mixture, half of chips and half of cheese. Repeat.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Bring to boil water and chicken cubes.
Add bite size broccoli pieces to water.
Melt butter in pan and add flour.
Stir into boiling water and stir until thickened and smooth.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Serve hot.
Great over baked potatoes for a potato bar.
Serves 14 (5 quarts).

title: dessert pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough onto Pizza pan and bake 5 to 7 minutes. Take out of oven and spread apple filling on top.
Combine nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine and stir well.
Sprinkle this on top of filling.
Put back in oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix confectionary sugar and milk together till smooth.
Pour on top while still hot.
Serves:
8 to 10 slices.

title: roquefort salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in blender.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Blend cheese in by hand or disregard.
Makes very good French dressing as is.

title: grandma's banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla & lemon juice. Add bananas. Sift salt, flour, soda, and baking powder; add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture. Fold in nuts. Pour into 2 greased & floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco and blend until it looks like coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and stir just enough to hold dough together.
Roll out onto floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 30 medium size biscuits.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O box, cooked or uncooked (cooked is better, uncooked is faster).
In casserole dish, place layer of vanilla wafers and layer of sliced bananas.
Spread 1/4 of pudding mix over layers.
Continue layers to make 4 to 5 layers.
Crumble 6 to 8 vanilla wafers and spread on top layer.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together yogurt, applesauce, powdered sugar, vanilla and cinnamon, nutmeg or ginger.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pineapple; heat 1 cup juice to boiling.
Add jello, stirring to dissolve.
Chill until syrupy.
Stir mayonnaise and softened cream cheese into jello.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Cut turkey into thin slices and then into strips about 3/4 inch wide.
In medium bowl, combine 3 teaspoons of the oil, lemon juice, garlic, chili pepper and oregano.
Add turkey and stir to coat.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add yellow and green peppers; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add turkey strips and stir-fry another 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato; heat 1 minute more.
Serve immediately in tortillas with salsa.
Serves 4.

title: chewies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add nuts and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Use 11 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Yields 24 chewies.

title: alison minute steak
directions: Cover steaks in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil in iron skillet.
Put steaks in baking dish.
Slice onion and pepper over steak.
Mix can of golden mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over steaks and onion and pepper.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 250°.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with coconut and English walnuts and set aside.
Beat egg whites, adding salt and vanilla gradually. Then add sugar, beating until the whites peak.
Fold the crumb mixture into the egg mixture and spread in a well-greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve plain or topped with ice cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix meal, eggs, oil, onion, buttermilk, corn and chili pepper. Pour half the batter into greased 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle half of cheese over batter.
Pour in remaining batter and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: pretzel bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over pretzels on a cookie sheet.
Make sure all pretzels are covered with mixture. Bake in a 200° oven for one hour.
Mix pretzels around at the half hour and continue to bake the remaining half hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger; drain grease.
Add garlic, tomatoes, tomato paste and basil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Cook noodles; layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese; repeat.
Bake 1/2 hour in hot oven 425°, and 1 hour in 350° oven.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter cookies from cake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then on to racks to cool.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In hot oil, cook chops until brown on both sides.
Remove chops from skillet.
Spoon off fat from skillet.
Combine soup and water in skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Return chops to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes, or until chops are no longer pink, stirring often.
Best when served over prepared rice.

title: chili sauce for weiners
directions: Saute chopped onion in 2 tablespoons of oil until light brown. Add hamburger and brown until done.
Then sprinkle in chili powder.
Add tomato juice and cook until thickness suited for weiners in rolls.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two bread pans (six cup capacity), 2 nine-inch cake pans or muffin tins.
Set aside. Combine first six ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Lightly beat the eggs; pour into well with oil, butter and water.
Stir batter until well combined.
Gently fold in the berries.
Pour batter into prepared pans; bake at least an hour for bread or cake pans, or until a toothpick or cake tester inserted into center comes out moist, but clean.
Check muffins for doneness at 20 minutes.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Blend until smooth. Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Mash flat with fork on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: parched peanuts
directions: Put peanuts in baking pan.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Put peanuts in oven; turn oven off.
Do not open oven door until oven has cooled all the way.
Peanuts will be done when the oven cools.

title: paella valenciana
directions: Saute garlic and
onion in olive oil.
Add rice and fry a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, chicken, ribs, shrimp, broth and wine and let
cook
for 30 minutes or until rice opens.
Decorate with peas
and
pimentos.
Cook in shallow frying pan in the oven at 375°.

title: italian ricotta cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in Ricotta.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Peel and seed tomatoes. Cube and chop or dice tomatoes, pepper and garlic.
In a large bowl, combine all chopped tomatoes, pepper, garlic, salt and herbs.
Gradually stir in olive oil, lemon juice and cold water.
Add all remaining ingredients. Chill for 4 hours. Cold and crunchy.

title: ample brown betty
directions: Toss bread cubes with oleo.
Divide half of the cubes among 4 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Arrange apples over bread, using 10 cups per pan.
Mix 2 cups brown sugar, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Divide into fourths and sprinkle over apples.
Mix water and lemon juice; pour a fourth into each pan.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Sprinkle remaining brown sugar equally over pans. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until frothy. Add sugar slowly and beat until smooth and glossy. Add white syrup and beat until firm peaks. Fold in vanilla.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in small bowl; set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar into large bowl. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Roll out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted oleo.
Fold over; brush tops with oleo.
Place on greased baking sheet; let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Make pudding using only 2 cups milk, and Dream Whip and let sit in refrigerator.
After cake has cooled, spread with cream cheese, then pineapple, then spread pudding, then Dream Whip and garnish with coconut.
This cake keeps well for about 2 days.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into cottage cheese; add crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl, preferably one with seal on lid.
Toss to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours, tossing occasionally to distribute marinade over vegetables.

title: cherry tart(no bake)
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and press in pan.
Whip cream cheese with sugar and milk.
Pour over crumbs.
Whip Dream Whip and pour over cheese mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and chocolate chips in small bowl and set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well; mixture will be soupy.
Fill paper lined muffin tins no more than 1/2 full with chocolate mixture.
Place 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture in center of chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tater tot supreme
directions: Place Tater Tots in bottom of casserole dish.
Put cooked and drained ground beef over potatoes.
Add soup and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are done, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Mix fruits together.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together; mix well and chill.

title: mexican chocolate pudding
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day:
In heavy 3-quart saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients; add next 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until chocolate is melted and mixture thickens slightly and boils, stirring frequently.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk slowly.
Mix well.
Cook over rapidly boiling water until well thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
When ingredients are well blended, pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix meat and noodles together; add Parmesan cheese, pizza sauce, salt, pepper and onion.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Put cheese on top for 5 minutes before taking out of oven.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel yams; cook until tender, not mushy (1/2-inch slices). Heat oven to 375°. Place in large 3-quart baking dish. Mix together remaining ingredients in heavy saucepan and bring to boil. Simmer 3 minutes. Pour over yams and bake 30 minutes, basting until well candied.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Cut down back of shrimp and remove black vein but not the shell.
Rinse and butterfly shrimp (spread open, shell still on). Place flat on cookie sheet and set aside.
Melt butter in medium skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute until soft.
Add broken shrimp and remaining ingredients and stir until mixed.
Mixture should be moist enough to mold when pinched.
Stuff each jumbo shrimp and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until shrimp becomes white.
Enjoy!

title: cumin-honey vinaigrette
directions: Combine first six ingredients in bowl.
Gradually whisk in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour to 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute sliced onions in the butter until tender.
Mix water, 2 cans of bouillon, and onions in saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add croutons or bread to soup bowl, add soup, top with cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese
come
to room temperature.
Mix with Bisquick and make into small
balls.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.

title: bisquick
directions: Combine all ingredients, cutting in shortening as small as possible.
Store in tightly covered container.
Can be used in Quickmix recipes, too.

title: low-fat creamy potato ham bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl,
combine potatoes, peas and ham.
In a small bowl,
combine parsley flakes, black pepper,
and mushroom soup.
Pour soup mixture over potato mixture and mix well to combine.
Pour into an 8 x 8 inch baking dish sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray.
Bake 25
- 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: crab meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Stir in cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder and spread over bottom of bread, then replace top. Wrap in a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated through. Cut into slices. Yield: 8 servings.

title: frozen corn
directions: Prepare young, tender corn.
Cut off cob.
Put in freezer container 4 cups corn, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add ice water to cover about 3/4 of corn.
Freeze.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Butter bread on 1 side.
Cube 7 slices and place on bottom of a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Fry sausages until crumbly. Grate cheese.
Whip salt, mustard, milk and eggs together. Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Put last 6 slices of buttered bread, cut in halves, on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Does not freeze well.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Add water.
Stir well.
Add flour.
Place in tightly covered bowl (will keep for several weeks in refrigerator).
Drop by spoonful into oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: home canned tomato soup
directions: Cook celery and onions in small amount of water.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until soft.
Put through food mill.
Add sugar and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and butter.
Cook together a while.
Stir into tomato mixture and heat to boiling. Fill pint jars.
Process 5 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Yield: 11 pints.

title: carrot stuff
directions: Alternate layers of carrots, onion and bell pepper. Make marinade of remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetables and chill at least 24 hours. Can be made several days ahead.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together macaroni, chopped olives, pimiento, eggs, onions and pickles.
Add dressing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in 3/4-inch cubes.
Add seasonings, then olive oil, only what the potatoes will absorb, then add vinegar and mix carefully until it is absorbed.
Mound on a bed of lettuce in a shallow dish.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and boil until thick.
Cool.
Mix in strawberries.
Put in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cook 3 minutes.
Spoon over saltine crackers.

title: mom's peach cake
directions: Prepare cake as per box instructions using two 9-inch round cake pans.
Strain peaches and reserve syrup.
Set aside 10 peach slices for cake topping.
Blend remaining peaches and set aside.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Mix corned beef and drained sauerkraut and the rest of the ingredients.
Top mixture with 16 ounces grated Swiss cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on buttered rye bread, open face.

title: chicken in chablis
directions: Sprinkle salt and nutmeg on both sides of breast.
Brown in butter on each side.
Add onions, mushrooms and 2/3 cup of wine. Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove chicken.

title: karen's broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil; add rice and simmer until tender.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet and saute onion with remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, biscuit mix and Cheddar cheese.
Roll in balls and place on rack in roasting pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter lengthwise or slice thick.
Cook about 20 minutes in lightly salted water until slightly tender.
Make syrup of butter, brown sugar, dash of salt and pepper and 1/2 cup of cooking water.
Coat potatoes with syrup and continue cooking.

title: italian goulash
directions: Brown beef chuck in olive oil; add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, egg and water.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding muffin mix last.
Pour into well-greased skillet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Wrap in foil.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all cheese at room temperature.
Cream together until smooth, adding remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until partially set. Form into ball and roll in very fine chopped nuts.
Return to refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, egg and onion in a bowl. Add some cracker crumbs.
Spoon mixture into hand and make a patty.
Roll in crumbs and fry.

title: refrigerator cucumber slices
directions: Shake well. Cover and keep in the refrigerator. Add additional cucumber as desired.

title: cookie bar(no sugar)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, boil 3 minutes and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheet, sprayed with oil, or 9 x 9-inch pan (as cake, then cut) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbara d's pie
directions: Mix and place in pie crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: white fudge balls
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Roll into balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter.
Place graham crackers in blender.
Blend crackers and butter.
Press mixture into 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Pour coconut, nuts and chocolate chips evenly over cracker mixture.
Pour sweetened, condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until coconut becomes lightly brown.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter or margarine over medium heat. Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with poppy seed egg noodles or fluffy rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Brown beef (if using); drain.
Add to remaining ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Bring to a boil the sugars and water.
Stir occasionally. Turn off and stir in maple flavoring.

title: sloppy jane sandwich filling
directions: Brown ground beef with diced onion in skillet over medium heat.
Drain ground beef mixture in colander and rinse in hot water to get rid of excess grease.
Return meat mixture to skillet and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer for approximately 20 minutes over low heat to blend flavors.
Serve on sandwich buns.

title: chocolate microwave fudge
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend).
Place butter on top of mixture in center of casserole.
Put in microwave on High power for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of casserole.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
If all butter has not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into waxed paper lined dish.
(Recipe can be doubled for thicker pieces of fudge. Cooking time will be approximately 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.)
Place in freezer 10 minutes until set.
Slice in squares and store.

title: company rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart round casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Fluff with fork before serving.

title: strawberry meringue roll
directions: Sift flour, 1/4 tsp salt and baking powder together.
Beat 4 egg whites stiff in large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 c sugar, gradually. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored in small bowl.
Add 1/4 c sugar and vanilla gradually.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites; fold in sifted ingredients.
Place on waxed paper lined 15x10-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 375 degrees.
Turn onto towel dusted with confectioners sugar.
Roll quickly as for jelly roll. Cool on rack.
Whip cream; fold in 2 Tbsp sugar and 1 c sliced strawberries.
Unroll meringue; frost with whipped cream mixture. Roll and chill.
Beat remaining egg white until stiff (or use Cool whip); add remaining sugar, 1/8 tsp salt and 3/4 c sliced strawberries.
Beat until stiff, at least 5 minutes.
Frost roll; decorate with whole strawberries immediately after frosting.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add taco seasoning according to package directions. Place in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish and allow to cool. Layer sour cream over ground beef. Layer refried beans over sour cream. Melt Velveeta cheese; add drained Ro-Tel and pour over beans. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Garnish with green pepper and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: miniature reuben sandwiches
directions: Cut Swiss cheese and corned beef into quarters.
Spread mustard on one side of bread and Thousand Island dressing on other.
Place Swiss cheese and corned beef and sauerkraut between slices.
Fry until brown.
Slice in half (or if you prefer leave whole).
May be prepared beforehand and frozen until ready to serve at which time place in oven for 10 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Place brisket in foil.
Leave room in foil for air space.
Put fat side of meat up.
Pierce meat like pie shell.
Put on sauce and salt and cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Open foil and add 2 cups barbecue sauce.
Bake for 2 more hours.
Cut meat on cross grain.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour, blending well. Stir eggs into mixture. Add margarine. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls on greased griddle or skillet. Cook until brown on both sides. Serve at once.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugars; add peanut butter and remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased cookie sheet with 1-inch side. Bake 25 minutes; remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
As they melt, spread as icing; cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add pineapple, sugar, carrots, oil and eggs.
Mix together well and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Reserve juice from pineapple for frosting.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix sugar and Fruit-Fresh.
Put over pears.
Cook until thick. Add crushed pineapple.
Cook 15 minutes longer.

title: hamburger wellington
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for ham, Swiss and rolls. Spread meat mixture on wax paper to form a rectangle slightly wider on one end.
Place ham and cheese on top and roll like a jelly roll. Cover with crescent roll dough. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: rice custard
directions: Add rice to milk in top of a double boiler.
Cook, covered, over boiling water until rice is tender, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly; add 1 1/2 tablespoons suar and salt.
Stir in some of the hot rice mixture.
Add to rest of rice mixture in double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and partially cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until quite stiff, then gradually add remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar, while continuing to beat until stiff.
Fold into rice custard.
Spoon into 4 to 5 dessert dishes. Top each with a cherry and a dribble of cherry juice.
Chill thoroughly.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook for 20 minutes at medium.
Top with corn chips, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Cream well.
Add milk, eggs, flour, vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in cold oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan with 4 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add milk and vegetables.
Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese and butter and season to taste.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently until cheese is melted and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy, not stiff. Stir in sugar, salt, and cinnamon. Add pecans and stir well, until pecans are completely coated. Spread nuts on large baking sheet, lined with aluminum foil sprayed with Pam. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 min. Remove form oven when dry and toasty. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Heat sugar, vinegar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture and chill. Eat with vegetables or hot dogs.

title: state of texas cookie
directions: In a large bowl cream the butter, margarine and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: old fashioned rhubarb pie
directions: Mix and cook slowly until like jelly; put in baked shell and cover with meringue made from egg whites (beaten stiff) and to which has been added 3 to 4 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: marie's pasta
directions: Cook the hamburger and Italian sausage on high and drain.
Add the tomatoes, garlic, parsley and basil. Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Add 1 box powdered sugar and 1 cup nuts.
Spread on while cake is hot.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water and wieners, then add water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add wieners and cook until good and hot.

title: strawberry or cherry salad
directions: Chop marshmallows up for a moister salad.
Pour milk over marshmallows.
Mix sugar in pineapple juice to dissolve.
Add to mixture.
Add strawberries, pecans and Cool Whip.
Stir real well! Refrigerate before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in oven at 250°.
Cook other ingredients for 10 minutes past boil, then stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
It will foam.
Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Precook pie crust at 400° for 2 to 3 minutes.
In skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Cook and drain spinach and cut into small pieces.
Add to skillet and mix.
Allow to cool. Beat eggs, milk and cream.
Add skillet mixture along with cheese and mix.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Thaw and rinse and then drain shrimp.
Cream together cream cheese and Italian dressing.
Add shrimp (I use about 2/3 of package).
Shape into ball.
Refrigerate.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir corn meal slowly into combined hot milk and water.
Add shortening, molasses and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into water; stir until dissolved.
Stir into corn meal mixture alternately with flour.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead about 7 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until double in size. Knead down; divide dough into two parts.
Shape each into a loaf. Let rise until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and Jell-O until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool, then add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Mix; pour into mold to congeal.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, pineapple juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Refrigerate until partially set (1/2 hour at least).
Remove and add 1 large cake, torn in 1 1/2 x 2-inch pieces.
Line a colander with Saran Wrap (over the holes).
Then layer cake, gelatine, etc. until all is used, leaving cake as the last layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Invert in plate and ice with small Cool Whip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli; pare stem and separate flowerets.
Cut stem in 1/2-inch slices. Cut potato into 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven until tender, about 3 minutes. Add curry powder, chicken broth, water and salt to kettle.
Bring to boil; add broccoli and potatoes.
Return to boiling; lower heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Puree mix in blender; do part at a time.
Reheat mix in large saucepan over low heat.
Stir in half and half.
Heat until piping hot.
Taste; add additional seasonings, if needed.

title: mama's fruit loop salad
directions: Mix jello and milk well in a rectangular pan.
Add all fruits, reserving about 12 mandarin slices.
Mix in the marshmallows, only enough to coat.
Spread on the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and reserved oranges.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to boil, turn down heat. Let simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: innocent daiquiri
directions: Blend ice, sweetener and canola oil in water until it is slushy.
Add strawberries and blend until they are diced and water turns red.
Add rum extract and blend on high for about 10 seconds. Add Hi-Energy Strawberry Supplement and blend approximately 5 seconds more.
Yum!

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Pour mixture into dish.
Save some cracker meal to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: breakfast caramel rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put rolls in pan.
Shake on regular pudding and pecans.
Boil margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over rolls and pudding.
Cover with a towel and let sit overnight.
In the morning, bake 1/2 hour at 350° until golden brown.
Turn upside down immediately.
Yummers!

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Tastes best when made the day before needed.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil over medium heat and cook onion until translucent. Add garlic, oregano, basil and tomatoes; heat until simmering.
Add salt and pepper; simmer until mixture reaches sauce consistency. Remove from heat and add parsley.
Serve, refrigerate for up to a week or freeze until needed.
A can of tomato paste can be added if you don't want to cook as long and want the sauce thicker.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour apple juice in percolator coffeepot.
Add sugar.
Fill coffee basket with red hots.
Perk as for coffee.
Serve hot.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Boil fryer until tender; debone and save broth.
Cook egg noodles in broth.
Put onion, celery and bell pepper in skillet and cook until tender.
Then add to cooked noodles and add chicken, soups and pimiento.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: howard's panocha
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and milk.
Cook in heavy saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves to soft ball stage (238°).
Cool at room temperature without stirring until lukewarm (110°).
Add
vanilla.
Beat
until mixture holds its shape and loses gloss.
Add nuts and quickly spread in greased pan.
Cool and eat and get fat!!

title: oreo surprise
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch pan put 17 to 20 Oreo cookies that have been finely crushed.
Squirt chocolate syrup generously on crumbs. Spread soft vanilla ice cream on top, about 1 pint.
Squirt a little more chocolate syrup on ice cream.
Then top that with 4-ounce container of Cool Whip and freeze.
Enjoy!

title: oatmeal meat loaf
directions: Beat egg well.
Add piece of loaf bread and squash it up good. Add all other ingredients.
Pat into 2 loaves and place in dish. Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Spread as much ketchup as you like on top.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine and chocolate. Stir constantly until smooth; remove from heat.
Cool slightly. Stir in flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder, salt and eggs; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Heat oven to 300°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 13 to 18 minutes, or until set.
Remove immediately from sheet and cool. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: crumbled chicken casserole
directions: Blend butter and stuffing; line a greased 5 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with half the crumbs.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: boston salad
directions: Combine jello, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Set until firm.

title: hot pasta
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Fry ground beef.
Add onion, garlic and pepper, then soy sauce.
Fry until hot.
Serve on top of noodles.

title: chicken terrific
directions: Mix soups, sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Add rice, green beans, water chestnuts, mushrooms and cheese. Add chicken last; mix well. Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Stir occasionally. Let stand about 15 minutes before serving.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place eggs in electric blender container; whirl until well beaten.
Mix flour with sugar.
Add to eggs with remaining ingredients.
Continue to whirl at high speed in blender until well combined.
Pour into 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done, trying not to brown it. Combine soups, water and uncooked rice in large baking dish. Lay chicken in mixture. Cook until rice is tender.

title: lemon sour cream cake
directions: Mix and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour; cook for 1 minute.
Add milk gradually and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add chicken broth; stir well.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in mustard, chicken, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes, or until heated through.
Ladle into soup bowls; sprinkle with croutons.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrots with onions
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine carrots, onion, water, thyme, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Stir once.
Add margarine and toss. Makes 4 servings.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for three minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly, then blend in sifted confectioners sugar.
If too thick, thin with a drop of hot water.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Put all ingredients except paprika in a cooking pot.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover.
Simmer on medium heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together well all but chocolate chips.
Pat out in 13 x 9-inch pan until smooth.
Melt 2 cups chocolate chips or candy bar pieces.
Spread over top.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: roasted and peeled chili(3 pints)
directions: Boil chili in mixture for 1 minute.
Pack in jars filled with juice.
Seal.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Pour oil over crackers.
Mix up all dry stuff.
Sprinkle over crackers.
Stir; put in tight can.
Make ahead.

title: honest john casserole
directions: Brown meat, green peppers and onion.
Boil noodles and add soups, cheese and mushrooms to meat mixture.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ground turkey and cheese made with skim milk can be used for low cholesterol diets.
This freezes well.

title: batter bread
directions: Beat eggs, meal, salt and 1 cup milk together well.
Thin with remaining milk.
Melt lard in the dish it is to be baked in and pour in the batter.
Last, add the soda.
Let the oven be hot when the bread is put in.

title: italian style pork chop and stuffing
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium-high.
Add chops; cook until browned on both sides.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, green pepper, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Stir stuffing mix and 1/2 cup of cheese into skillet.
Place chops over stuffing.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: bertie mae's fabulous dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together.	Spread over pie crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with pie mix.
Chill overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Take 2 cups of mixture and pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, oleo and Pet milk in double boiler.
Pour over partially baked cake mix and then add chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Pour rest of cake batter over all of this.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken roast
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Coat chicken with paprika.
Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken; lower heat.
Add the amount of vegetables you need for your family. Cover and cook 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour and water until smooth; pour into drippings for gravy.

title: dutch almond slices(jan hagel)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the butter and margarine for 30 seconds. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolk; beat well.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Clean shrimp and break up.
Chop onion and celery.
Heat soup just until it boils.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water and pour it into the soup.
Turn off soup mixture and add the other ingredients.
Set at least 6 hours.

title: deluxe hash browns
directions: Place potatoes, soups, onions, green pepper, sour cream, salt & pepper into a large mixing bowl. Let stand until you can mix the ingredients together. Place in greased 9 x 13 glass pan. Sprinkle with parsley flakes & paprika. Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 inch cake pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
While the cake is still hot, use a fork and poke holes all over the cake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: blueberry salad(poland)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water. Cool.
Add blueberries and grapes.
Pour into ring mold.
Serve with sour cream in center of ring.
Yields 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese(crock-pot)
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; put in crock-pot.
Add butter and 2 cups cheese; stir.
Add milk, beaten eggs, can of milk, salt and pepper.
Pour in crock-pot and stir.
Top with 1/2 cup of cheese and cover.
Cook 3 hours on low heat.

title: microwave barbecue beans
directions: Cover bacon with a paper towel.
Cook until done.
Remove bacon and cook onions in bacon drippings on High for 3 minutes. Add other ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 10 minutes. Stir twice.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; break into chunks.
Mix into soup the following: celery, onion, mayo, almonds and chicken.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with 1/4-inch stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Make a day ahead or can be frozen.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, put 1 large can pineapple tidbits (drained), the strawberries, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and the sliced bananas.
Mix well, but gently.
Combine with the cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into a large loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.
This may be tightly sealed and kept in the freezer for 3 or 4 months.
You may line the pan with whole graham crackers and cover the top with graham crackers, this is much better.

title: macaroni and cheese pizza
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburg or 1/2 pound hamburg and 1/2 pound sausage.
Can put in handful of pepperoni (optional), 1 jar chunky Prego sauce and 1 package Mozzarella cheese.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in macaroni and cheese that has been prepared according to directions on package.
Pour eggs, onion and peppers over macaroni and cheese.
Next, put layer of meat, next layer of Prego sauce, then cheese.
(Watch so cheese doesn't burn.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach swirls
directions: Make syrup by boiling 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix milk, egg and shortening; add dry ingredients.
Mix to soft dough.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick. Spread fruit over dough.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 9 slices.
Place cut side down in pan of syrup.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix in large bowl.
Add applesauce, eggs, salt and flavoring.
Beat 3 minutes until smooth.
Combine nuts, coconut and cherries with 3/4 cup flour.
Stir in batter until well mixed.

title: wife's delight
directions: Brown beef and pour off the fat.
Add seasoning and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Combine onions, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Drain all beans and add to pork and beans.
Put into 2-quart casserole. Saute bacon and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt clarine's tomato pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until set (about 30 minutes).

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots, using large holes of grater.
In a large bowl, combine carrots, raisins and pineapple.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise and powdered sugar until well blended.
Pour over carrot mixture and toss lightly to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: nana's apple pie
directions: Blend flour and Crisco, and add water and salt until dough is moist.
Roll into a ball and set aside.
Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out ball of pastry for 2 crusts.
Put bottom crust into 9-inch pie plate and fill with apple mixture.
Dot with teaspoon of butter.
Top with second crust.
Flute edges and place small slits to let moisture escape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Add extract.
Grease and flour tube pan or 8 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Add half of cranberry sauce on batter.
Add remainder of batter and rest of sauce on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
