Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done; top with glaze.

title: date muffins
directions: Combine in one bowl the chopped dates, butter or margarine, boiling water and soda.
Now add, beating in well, the egg and vanilla.
Sift in next, stirring only until smooth, the sugar and sifted flour.
Add last 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in muffin tins.

title: stuffed green peppers with chicken and vegetables
directions: Saute oil, butter, dry seasonings, chicken broth and chicken strips until 3/4 done.
Blanch green peppers and cut off tops (remove seeds).
Do this first.
Remove chicken from pan (save saute mixture).
In same pan, saute broccoli, red pepper and mushrooms until cooked but firm.
Dice chicken.
Mix chicken, vegetables and bread crumbs together.
Firmly pack mixture into green peppers.
Bake in shallow dish at 350° for 20 minutes checking occasionally that peppers are keeping their shape.
Just before removing, sprinkle Romano cheese and cook 5 more minutes. Serve with baked or roasted potatoes.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Brown onion in butter; add flour and mix.
Add water and corn and cook until it thickens.
Add milk, salt, butter and dash of pepper.
Heat to boiling point.
Serve hot.
Can be served with bacon bits sprinkled on top.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots and coconut together.
Add milk and sugar to fruit mixture, a little at a time.
Shape into marble size balls; roll in confectioners sugar.
Easy and very good!

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and caramels.
Roll into logs and chill.
Melt caramels in top of double boiler or microwave.
Pour into large plate.

title: garden chicken noodle soup(microwave recipe)
directions: Place chicken in deep 3-quart casserole.
Add water.
Stir in peas and next 7 ingredients.
Cover with heavy duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 20 to 25 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in noodles.
Reduce to medium (50% power).
Cover and microwave for 20 to 30 minutes or until noodles and chicken are tender, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix above.
Chill in refrigerator overnite.
Great with fresh fruit when available.

title: feather rolls
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine warm milk and butter.
When butter is melted, gradually add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add rest of flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Raise to double in size.
Make into rolls.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix egg, milk and pumpkin thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin tins or baking cups half full.
Bake at 400 for 20 minutes.
Makes 12-18 Muffins.

title: oven fried oysters
directions: Mix well flour, salt and pepper.
Roll oysters in flour, then dip in eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle both sides of oysters with oil.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: keftedes(greek meat balls)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into small balls or large flat cakes.
Roll in flour and fry in hot vegetable oil.
Makes 30 small keftedes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all the ingredients with enough buttermilk to make it smooth.
Spoon by teaspoonfuls in hot grease and cook until browned.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions (sliced) and salt in 2 quarts water and 4 trays of ice.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Drain cucumbers and onions and add to other mixture.
Bring to a full boil and remove from heat and pack in jars.

title: hawaiian "sausages"
directions: Bring to boil in large Dutch oven pan the barbecue sauce, brown sugar, hot seasoning salt, juice off the pineapple and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut chicken wieners in 1-inch pieces and add.
Boil for 10 minutes until wieners plump up (pan will be full).
Add pineapple and cook another 2 minutes.
May be transferred to crock-pot to keep warm until served.

title: busy day burgers
directions: Brown and season hamburger meat to taste. Drain excessive fat from heat.
Put can of onion soup into meat.
Heat and serve on the buns.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Slowly heat pumpkin and butter together until butter is melted.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; add to pumpkin.
Beat eggs well; add cream and flavoring.
Then fold in stiffly beaten eggs. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese and bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese out on baking dish.
Spread chili beans and top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until bubbling. Serve with nacho chips.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Make a crumb mixture of the first 5 ingredients and put half of it in a greased 9 x 9 pan.

title: pistachio supreme
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana whip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into two tall glasses filled with ice.

title: german kraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse kraut.
Mix all ingredients.
Add sugar to vinegar.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over other ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and save.
Mix pineapple with marshmallows in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar, egg and vinegar.
Place this mixture in a saucepan, heating it until thick.
Place in refrigerator to cool. When cool, mix with Cool Whip.
Fold Cool Whip mixture into marshmallow and pineapple mixture.
Add apples and peanuts.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Cream together margarine and confectioners sugar.
Mix in chopped pecans and bourbon.
Cool in refrigerator.
Roll in small balls.
Put in freezer until next day or whenever you want to dip them.
Take out of freezer and dip in prepared melted chocolate, butter and melted paraffin in top of double boiler or in dipping chocolate you can buy.

title: cream cheese salsa dip
directions: Press cream cheese into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour salsa over top; sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese bubbles.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Sprinkle with chili powder, salt and sugar and mix well.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Mix together oil and flour.
Add to meat mixture.
Add beans.
Simmer until heated, 30 minutes.

title: blueberry banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray muffin tins with vegetable oil.
In a bowl, combine flours, sugar, wheat germ, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir until well mixed; set aside.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Combine pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle dry jello and nuts.
Let set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries, grate orange (peel and all) and chop celery (very fine).
Mix Jell-O with water and mix all ingredients well. Place in a ring pan or jello mold (it will make a prettier salad). Add nuts if you want (1/2 cup walnuts).

title: homemade finger paint
directions: You will need white shelf paper.

title: thrifty meat pie
directions: Heat fat and add onion, chicken, green pepper, soup, milk and salt.
Cook until mixture reaches boiling point.
Pour in casserole dish.
Make dough of flour, baking powder, salt, oil and 2/3 cup milk and mix well until blended.
Roll between waxed paper.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over dough; roll up and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place on top of casserole in pinwheel design. Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave-proof bowl at 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Stir constantly until melted and smooth.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crumbs.
Use 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top mixture with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german beef stew
directions: Melt shortening in a Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Place onions on top of meat.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute zucchini and onions until golden brown and tender.
In large bowl, beat together egg white and milk.
Stir in muffin mix and blend until smooth.
Fold in zucchini and onions with 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Melt remaining cheese on top.
Cool.
Serve with Olive Spread.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add the sugar, water and corn syrup. cook over medium heat, stirring. Bring mixture to 290° on a cooking thermometer (soft crack stage).
Quickly stir in 1/2 cup chopped almonds.
Pour mixture onto ungreased baking sheet. Wait 2 or 3 minutes for surface to firm.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips. When the chips have softened, spread the chocolate evenly over surface.
Sprinkle on remaining almonds.
Store covered.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) clear plastic cups.

title: "spaghetti della casa"(specialty from da vittorio's, nutsford, england)
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add ham or bacon; saute quickly.
Add sauce or puree; stir in cream.
Allow sauce to cook down and thicken.
Add more sauce and/or cream, if desired (sauce should be orange-pink).
Toss in cooked peas.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in 3 quart pan.
Add beaten eggs,
cheese,
salt,
onion
and
chopped broccoli to melted butter.
Stir in corn bread mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan or
dish.
Bake
at
for 40 to 45 minutes or until fork inserted comes out clean.

title: chantilly dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together; store in refrigerator.
Use as a dip for any fresh fruit.
Great with strawberries!

title: baked pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix seeds, oil and salt.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes at 250° or until crisp.

title: golden russets
directions: Cook potatoes in salted, boiling water until tender.
Remove from water, cool and grate coarsely.
Combine and add sour cream, grated cheese, onion, milk, salt and pepper and mix well.
Place in a well-greased baking pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and add bread crumbs.
Mix well and scatter on top of potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean topper
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand for a few hours.
Eat on top of beans or peas.
Adds a fresh vegetable taste to your meal.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add cake flour, eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Don't preheat oven.

title: blue ribbon zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon together.
Form a hole in the center.
Mix eggs, margarine, zucchini, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Add to mixed dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir syrup, salt, peanuts and sugar in 1 1/2-quart bowl. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High and stir.
Cook 3 minutes on High; add butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until caramel colored.
Add baking soda and pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F (180° C). Mix all the ingredients together with a mixer until well blended. Roll dough into round small balls. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool completely, then roll in additional confectioners sugar. Makes 42 cookies.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar and margarine or butter.
Beat eggs and vanilla, then add.
Spread over the bananas.
Spread pineapple over the powdered sugar mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese
reach
room temperature.
Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls
or logs and then roll in chopped parsley or chopped nuts.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with mixer. Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar 1 cup at a time, beating well on medium speed. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often. When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry. Add milk a teaspoon at a time, mixing at medium speed until light and fluffy. Can be stored in covered container in refrigerator 2 weeks. Re-whip before using. Makes 3 cups.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Put all ingredients, except crabmeat in blender container. Cover and set to "Blend" until smooth.
Stop and push ingredients toward blades when necessary.
Add broken up crabmeat.
Cover and set to "Chop" until crabmeat is chopped (not too long).
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh chilled vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Add eggs.
Fold in zucchini and melted butter.
Prepare like pancakes.

title: terrence's super snack
directions: Spread Fluff on each cracker, then put them together and eat! They are the best!

title: swedish shrimp
directions: Saute onions in oil in a nonstick skillet to soften, 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup broth, bring to a boil.
Add shrimp. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, until shrimp are pink, 3 minutes. Whisk together 1/4 cup broth, sour cream, mustard and cornstarch in cup until smooth.
Whisk into skillet.
Cook, stirring, to thicken.
Add pepper, dill and lemon juice.

title: dump cake
directions: Put apples in the bottom of dish, then crushed pineapple, then the dry cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth; beat in egg and vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Combine pecans with reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly. Cool. Chill.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with egg mixture.
Add vanilla and zucchini. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: lazy susy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish in oven.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk in a bowl.
Pour over butter; pour fruit over that.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: nut cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugars and then other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach preserve cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix ingredients as listed.
When batter is smooth, fold in pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients, cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk and form in ball.
Knead on floured board 1 minute.
Pat 3/4-inch thick, cut in rounds.
Cook at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat french fry
directions: Coat sliced potatoes in egg white sauce in a bowl.
Coat well. Put potatoes on a baking sheet.
Spray lightly with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Contains 1 gram of fat per
serving.

title: seen's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo.
Mix with eggs and sugar.
Pour into greased platter.
Let set a while in refrigerator.
Then cut.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix seasonings an meat until "mushy."
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and shape meat mixture into 4 loaves approximately 2 1/2 inches in diameter and 9 inches long. Be sure to compress the loaves to get all the air out.
Bake in roaster pan on drip rack for 4 hours at 225°.
After 2 hours, turn loaves over.
Let cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoon and bake at 350° until done.

title: brunswick stew *
directions: Have chicken well done and boned.
Beans, corn and tomatoes can be fresh or canned.
Mix all ingredients together, including the chicken gravy and cook slowly until well done.
The sugar should be added just before coming off the stove, as it may make the stew stick to bottom of pan.
Should make about 6 quarts.

title: bubble formula
directions: Combine into a solution and allow to sit in an open container for one day.
Suggested items to make bubbles include hoops, can rings, juice cans, coat hanger shapes, slinkies, your fingers; use your imaginations!

title: aunt opal's pan rolls
directions: Scald milk; add milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add egg, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add another 1/4 cup flour.
Stir in rest of flour with a spoon until dough is stiff enough to handle.
Let dough rise until double in size.
Place on a lightly floured board and knead gently for 1 minute.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and cheese turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Press or roll to a 5-inch circle.
Combine browned sausage, seasoning, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese. Spoon about 3 tablespoons mixture into center of each flattened biscuit.
Fold dough in half over filling.
Press edges with a fork to seal.
Brush tops with egg and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff with salt and vanilla.
Then slowly and steadily, beat in the Karo.
Pour over anything of your choosing.

title: potato boats
directions: Scrub and quarter potatoes lengthwise.
Place in foil lined baking dish.
Brush with oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 400° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sunny-side-up casserole
directions: Slice half of cheese to cover bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Grate other half and set aside.
Mix seasonings with sour cream.
Pour half the mixture over cheese.
Layer crumbled sausage over sour cream.
Break whole eggs on top of sausage.
Spread on remaining sour cream.
Dollop without breaking eggs.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 325 for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: "shoney's" strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil; cook until thick. Cool for 15 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Line baked pie shell with strawberries.
Pour mixture over berries.
When ready to serve, top with dollops of Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: stir and roll biscuits(makes 12 to 16 biscuits)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Pour oil into a measuring cup; fill the cup with milk.
Make a depression in flour.
Pour in milk mixture all at once.
Stir with steel fork until dough no longer clings to side of bowl.
Pat to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick in rectangular pan or casserole dish.
Cut, then bake at 400° to 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: deanna's grape-nuts pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scald milk, butter and sugar; let it cool slightly.
Add Grape-Nuts.
Beat eggs slightly; add vanilla and salt.
Add egg mixture to milk mixture.
Slowly place in buttered casserole.
Put casserole in pan of warm water.
Bake at 375° for about 1/2 hour or until lightly browned.

title: susan's favorite party mix
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Measure dry cereals, pretzels, nuts, etc. to make 9 - 10 cups.
Place into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Slowly pour dressing mix over dry cereals and mix to coat.

title: krusciki(polish crullers)
directions: Beat egg yolks in bowl until thick; add salt and vanilla. Continue beating.
Add cream and flour alternately until well blended.
Turn on floured board.
Cover, allow to rest for 10 minutes.
Knead until dough begins to blister (about 5 minutes). Roll out thin and cut into strips 1-inch wide and 4 inches long. Cut a gash in the center and twist ends through.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until lightly browned.
Drain on absorbent paper.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter corn flake goodies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Add the peanut butter, then stir in corn flakes.
Mix and drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients and butter.
Add eggs, milk and cherries.
Bake.
Serve warm with milk.

title: italian gumbo
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pot; simmer until tortellini is tender.
This is a very thick soup, almost like a stew.
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: ranch vegetables
directions: Mix dry Hidden Valley Ranch milk recipe original dressing mix with the oil and add frozen vegetables; toss.
Add 1 package at a time.
Cook in casserole dish in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin orange cheese pie
directions: Prepare pie
crust with a high fluted edge.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer, until light and fluffy.
Beat
in
eggs,
one
at
a
time.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg,
orange rind and pumpkin until smooth.
Pour mixture into prepared pastry shell.
Place in a preheated 425° oven; lower temperature to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool
completely
on
wire
rack.
Just before serving, top with sour cream and halved Glaceed Orange Slices. Sprinkle with pistachio nuts.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight jar.
Use 2 rounded teaspoonfuls for a cup of hot water.

title: ants on a log
directions: Wash and cut celery into small pieces (let an adult help). Fill with peanut butter.
Place raisins on top.
Eat!

title: mississippi mud drops
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in microwave (about 2 1/2 minutes, stop and stir).
Add milk, flour and vanilla.
Drop onto foil-lined cookie sheet.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Combine next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Add peas, egg and mayonnaise and mix gently.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut creams
directions: Combine cream cheese frosting and cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add confectioners sugar, 1 cup at a time, stirring until thoroughly blended after each addition. Place large sheet of waxed paper on work surface.
Pour coconut on waxed paper.
Form level 1/2 tablespoonfuls of candy into balls. Roll each ball in coconut.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Yields 3 pounds of candy.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine dry ingredients; add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk. Spread in a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. Cut into squares; split each piece in half horizontally. Spoon whipped cream and strawberries onto bottoms; replace tops. Garnish with more berries and whipped cream. Serve immediately. Yield: 9 servings.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine noodles, drain and place aside.
Combine butter and whipping cream in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts.
Stir in cheese, pepper and parsley.
Pour mixture over hot fettuccine and toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pretzel pie
directions: In blender or processor, crush pretzels.
In a bowl, mix pretzel crumbs, sugar and butter until well blended.
Form a crust in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool or freeze.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly in a medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except blueberries, just until moistened. Fold blueberries into batter.
Divide batter evenly among cups. Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the salt.
When this mixture is hot, add remaining sugar, mixed with flour.
Cook until thick.
Place half of mixture in bowl.
Top with bananas and wafers.
Repeat.
Yields 6 or 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Steam broccoli until tender.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix Cheez Whiz and broccoli, then add onion and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch or flour, sugar and salt. Add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add small amount to eggs.
Stir into remaining mixture and cool for 1 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix altogether.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, then add beaten egg whites and brown.
Cook on lower rack.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Cover green beans with hot water and place in oven covered. cook at 450 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare rice; set aside.
Saute the celery and onion in margarine.
Mix everything together.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: out of this world dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool before adding second layer.
Mix Cool Whip, crushed pineapple (drained), strawberry pie filling and condensed milk together and pour into cooled baked crust.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours.
Best overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Pour over cake.
Spread over top.
Bake 35 minutes.
When taken out of oven, put sauce on cake while hot.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine eggs, butter, milk and vinegar.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out very thin on floured surface.
Let stand until dough is no longer sticky, but not brittle.
Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick, Spread out and allow to dry, about 2 hours.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together cake mix, pudding, eggs, milk and chocolate bits.
Make sure the ingredients are well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: south carolina hash
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with onions and green pepper.
Drain off grease and return to skillet.
Add whole tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir until it is well blended.
Reduce heat to simmer and cover.
Simmer for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Serve hash over rice when it is done.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together the first five dry ingredients.
Add eggs and orange juice concentrate.
Add vegetable oil with enough boiling water to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add oil and eggs.
Combine spices, soda, salt and flour and add to apple mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Cook 1 hour at 350° and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Layer
in
baking
dish 1/2 of potatoes, 1/2 of onions, 1/2 of cabbage and 1/2 of corned beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Repeat.
Mix
bacon drippings and water and pour over top.	Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into pieces and put into a large greased baking dish. In a bowl, beat eggs, add sugar and mix well. Add milk and evaporated milk, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Stir in melted butter. Sprinkle raisins and coconut over bread pieces and pour egg mixture over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat together Crisco, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: mom's meat loaf recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until thoroughly combined. Spray muffins tins with Pam.
Fill each space 1/2 - 2/3 full of meat mixture.
Bake at 375 for approx. 10 mins.
Pour approx. 1 tsp. ketchup on top of each meat section then continue to bake for approx. 5 more minutes.
Cool approx. 5 mins.
Then remove meat from pans.

title: sesame fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk and egg mixture; then in flour mixture. Melt 1/2 cup butter in baking pan.
Place chicken, skin side down, in single layer in pan.
Bake 1/2 hour in 400° oven; turn and bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: sausage cake
directions: Cover the cup of raisins with boiling water and let set. Cream sugar and sausage together.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add sugar and sausage mixture alternately with dry ingredients to buttermilk.
Drain raisins and add raisins and nuts to mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Top with caramel frosting.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all together with egg beater until smooth.

title: chili and beans
directions: Layer in crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Ideal to cook on low overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread 1 can of crescent rolls on bottom of cake pan and bake as directed.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise and spread on baked crust.
Top with raw vegetables cut into small pieces. Sprinkle with your favorite shredded cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown
onion
and
ground beef.
Add other ingredients. Simmer on
top of stove for 1 hour or bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss macaroni with milk; cover and chill.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, pepper and dissolved bouillon mixture.
Stir into macaroni. Fold in onion, pepper, pickle and dill weed.
Chill.

title: calypso salad(aka southwest bean salad)
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix well.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: ralph's linguini with mushrooms and lemon sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter and water until tender. Add lemon juice and seasonings.
Cook linguini as directed on box. Drain.
Serve sauce hot over linguini.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, heat soup, margarine, salt, pepper, milk and onions.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Mix with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: leo's hermit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in the coffee. Add the dry ingredients.
Fold in the raisins.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: The day before serving, boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel, dice and salt to taste while still warm.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator with dressing.
Next day, add eggs, celery and onion. Mix with mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Serves 20.

title: great grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil 2 cups water and 2 cups raisins for 5 minutes.
Cool and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Cream together shortening, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix in flour, vanilla, baking powder, salt and oatmeal.
(Use of chopped nuts is optional.) Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fiesta party dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: mexican platter
directions: Spread refried beans on a small platter, then add lettuce (if you use guacamole, it goes on the lettuce).
Add chopped veggies; top with shredded cheese.
Add taco seasoning to sour cream to taste.
Mound this on top of cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy eggs earl egg casserole
directions: Layer bottom of a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan with Pepperidge Farm thin sliced bread (crust removed).
Layer with small cubes of ham (sausage, bacon, etc.).
Cover with Swiss cheese and shredded Cheddar cheese.
I alternate the layers.
Pour over the above: eggs, milk, onion powder and garlic powder.
Refrigerate overnight (covered) and remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Before baking, spread corn flakes over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (lower temperature for glass pan).

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Beat eggs and gradually add to hot mixture, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Place oil in a 12 x 8-inch glass dish.
Dip each tortilla in oil, coating lightly.
Lay flat in dish.
Microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until steamy hot.
Stack tortillas on plate and set aside.
Combine onion and water in a 6-cup glass measuring cup.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in soup and chilies.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly, stirring once.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Spread 1/2 cup of mixture evenly in dish used for heating tortillas.
Place about 1 tablespoon soup mixture down center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll up around filling and place seam side down in baking dish.
Pour remaining soup mix over tortillas. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 7 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: plain jane cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs and flavorings.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Place cake in a cold oven.
Turn heat to 340° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: family meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: In medium-large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, 3 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion; drain.
Place in 2-quart microwavable casserole dish.
Add spaghetti sauce, macaroni and boiling water.
Stir and microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High for 6 more minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and let sit for 1 minute before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, place 1/2 stick butter, salt, onion, water and broccoli; cook until dry.
Add celery soup, garlic cheese, milk and cooked rice.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into patties or croquettes.
Fry until done.

title: sausage dip
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in a large frypan.
Drain grease. Add diced tomatoes and cream cheese.
Stir together and simmer to melt cream cheese.
Serve warm and dip with nacho chips.

title: raspberry ice cream parfait pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot liquid in 2-quart saucepan.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls until melted.
Chill until thickened but not set.
Fold in drained fruit.
Tun into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip and fruit.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done, but not overcooked. Let cool.
Peel and dice potatoes, onion, green pepper, celery and eggs.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.

title: basic cocoa cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients in another mixing bowl.
Add to first mixture and mix at medium with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
I like to add 3/4 cup ground walnuts to batter before I bake the cake.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and butter. Heat and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add milk, oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and chill until firm.

title: orange-almond ambrosia
directions: To toast the almonds, spread them on a baking sheet and place in a 350° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.
Peel and section the oranges. Place the honey in a small bowl.
In another bowl, combine the cereal and toasted almonds.
Brush each orange section with honey, using a pastry brush, then lightly roll each section in the cereal-nut mixture.
Arrange on a serving dish or individual plates.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: almond cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 10-inch tube pan.
Press almonds into butter on both bottom and sides.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: corn meal cups
directions: Lightly grease six 8 ounce souffle dishes or custard cups. Line with heavy-duty foil and generously grease.
In a large saucepan, bring 3 1/2 cups water, bouillon, butter and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Gradually stir in corn meal.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and egg.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Press about 3/4 cup corn meal mixture to line bottom and side of foil liner in each prepared dish.
Crimp edges of corn meal mixture, if desired. Bake for 25 minutes or until edges are light golden.
Makes 6 cups.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Mixture should be extra stiff. Line bottom of medium-size loaf pan with wax paper.
Pack batter firmly.
Wrap pan in foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad(mexican style)
directions: Chop all ingredients (except mayonnaise) by hand or in a Cuisinart until finely chopped.
Add mayonnaise; more if desire a creamier texture.
Serve immediately or chill until a later time.

title: celery salad(goi can tay)
directions: Soak the celery, carrot, salt and ginger in ice water for 1/2 hour (no more than
1 hour) and drain.
Add cooked chicken and mix.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Mix soy sauce, m.s.g. and sesame seed oil when time to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Sift
flour with sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in cornmeal.
Add
eggs,
milk
and
shortening.
Beat until just smooth.
(Do
not overbeat.) Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Blend one half of ingredients in a blender or with a hand mixer and pour into ice cream freezer.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: oven cornflake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix melted margarine, flour and soup mix.
Dip chicken in mixture and then roll in crushed cornflakes. Put in pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Sprinkle in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add pizza sauce over meat; sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Press with fork before cooking or place chocolate kiss in the middle immediately after taking out of oven.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan and bake for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mash cranberry sauce with potato masher; combine with gelatin.
Add celery, apple and nuts. Pour into mold (spray it with Pam) and refrigerate overnight. Unmold and serve.
This is a great salad.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In large saucepan, heat sugar, butter and milk to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats and/or coconut and nuts.
Drop by scant tablespoon onto waxed paper or foil.
If mixture is too stiff, stir in 1 or 2 drops of milk.
If mixture is too thin, stir in oats or coconut.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen candies.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Lay 2 slices of apple on a crescent roll.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; roll up and place in a baking dish.
Heat remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture with oleo until sugar melts. Pour over apple roll-up.
Pour Mountain Dew over roll ups and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soupa avgolemono(egg and lemon soup)
directions: In a 3 or 4 quart saucepan, bring stock to a boil over high heat.
Pour in the rice; reduce the heat to low and simmer uncovered for about 15 minutes or until grains are just tender but still slightly resistant to the bite.
Reduce heat.
Beat the eggs with a whisk or rotary beater until frothy.

Beat in the lemon juice and stir in about 1/4 cup of the simmering chicken broth. Then slowly pour the mixture into the broth, stirring constantly. Cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes, or until soup thickens enough to coat the spoon lightly.
Do not let the soup come to a boil or the eggs will curdle.
Add salt to taste and serve at once, garnished with mint.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown sausage and add to spaghetti sauce.
Heat thoroughly. In a bowl, mix 1 egg, the Ricotta cheese, the drained spinach and about 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Cook shells according to package.
Drain with cold water.

title: mr. f's funny feet frypan fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt and milk in an electric frypan.
Set dial at 275°.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Turn off frypan and add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until chips and marshmallows are melted. Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: pineapple-cheese bake
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese in bowl; mix well. Spoon into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Serve warm as side dish or dessert.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough, but don't permit to rise.
Break one loaf in small pieces and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: garden muffins
directions: Grease 24 muffin tins.
In a large bowl, stir together the dry ingredients and vegetables.
In separate bowl, beat together the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Pour over the dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour batter into muffin tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring; beat 5 minutes.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Add to potatoes the bread crumbs, butter, egg, salt and sage. Add the salt pork and onion. Stuff turkey or goose.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and cook at 300° until brown on top.

title: microwave puppy chow
directions: Measure out ingredients from list of ingredients.
Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Then pour cereal mixture into large resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely. Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store leftovers in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp and fish casserole(serves 8)
directions: Soak fish fillets in milk for 3 hours (can be done overnight). Dredge in flour and brown in butter.
Place in casserole.
Saute onions and bell peppers in butter until soft.
Add shrimp and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add soup, mushrooms, lemon juice, sherry and mushroom juice, Lea & Perrins, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour over fish and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
May be prepared ahead of time and put in refrigerator.

title: low-fat low sodium potato soup
directions: Cook onion in oil, stirring frequently, until softened but not browned.
Scoop potato from skins.
Puree one potato and milk in blender until smooth.
Pour into saucepan.
Add onion, remainder of potato, salt and pepper.
Heat to simmering over medium heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 servings, 1 cup each.

title: snowball salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and refrigerate.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix cloves, cinnamon, salt and sugar; add to eggs.
Fold in sour cream and raisins; pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, cover and store in refrigerator. Pinch off amount needed.
Roll out and cut.
These do not have to rise before baking. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: jesus birthday cake(aka john's nut bread)
directions: Put all chopped ingredients in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and coat with flour.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla to eggs. Fold into dry ingredients until well mixed.
Place in a meat loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Yields 1 (3 pound) cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle top with 1/2 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomato sauce and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain. Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add noodles and coat with sour cream/cream cheese mixture.
Layer sauce and noodles in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch
directions: Boil sugar, molasses, vinegar and water together for 2 minutes, then add the butter and keep on boiling, without stirring, until mixture becomes brittle when tried in cold water.
Pour into a buttered pan; when nearly cool, cut with a sharp knife.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add chicken, lettuce, corn, mayonnaise and vegetables; mix in large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tostadas or crackers.

title: honey glazed curry chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Rub the chicken with the garlic. Discard the garlic.
Place the chicken pieces on a baking sheet. In a small saucepan, bring the honey, wine and curry powder to a boil.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes until thick.
Brush the chicken with the glaze.
Roast for 10 minutes; brush with glaze and keep roasting until chicken is completely done, about 15 minutes more for the thighs and 10 minutes more for the breasts.
Before serving, sprinkle the chicken with chives.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Put everything together. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Use with chips, corn chips or Doritos.

title: savory crescent chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese and butter.
Add chicken, milk, chives, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Pour into casserole dish and top with crescent rolls.
Bake until brown on top.
Delicious!

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: In large bowl, mix sour cream, both soups, chopped onion, jalapeno (chopped) and grated cheese.
Put filling into tortillas and roll up.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix all together except chocolate chips.
Shape into small balls.
Put in freezer about 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Add a little cooking wax to make thin.
Take toothpick and put in center of each ball. Dip into melted chocolate until half covered.
Put on wax paper.
Let cool. (Should look like a buckeye.)

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Drain pimentos.
Chop finer, if desired.
Put Ro-Tel peppers in blender for about 2 seconds.
Mix with melted cheese.
Use favorite chips.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Place gelatine in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Boil soup, then whip the cream cheese through soup.
Add gelatine soaked in water.
Let mixture cool.
Add mayonnaise, chopped vegetables and shrimp.
Add seasonings.
Cool until molded.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Make paste of cocoa and vinegar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Blend well.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Bake in three layer pans at 350° until done.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Layer pineapple, coconut and pecans in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix over top.
Dot with sliced margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken.
Combine mayonnaise, water chestnuts and soup. Add chicken and place in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter and combine with stuffing.
Pat this mixture over the chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate refreshers
directions: Mix
flour with
soda
and
salt;
set	aside.	Combine dates, brown sugar,
water and butter in large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until dates soften.
Remove from heat. Stir
in chocolate chips.
Blend in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with
orange
juice and milk.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter
in	greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25	to
30	minutes.
Cool	and
spread with Orange Glaze.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix together; pour half of batter into tube pan.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and 2 teaspoons brown sugar over mixture. Pour remaining mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Grease and flour pans lightly.

title: hamburger and rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion in skillet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add rice, cream of celery soup, water and soy sauce to hamburger.
Mix well.
Cover skillet or transfer food to a baking dish and bake one hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Whip.
Good dip for broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Fill tube pan half full and sprinkle nuts on top. Bring butter, brown sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil, spray with Pam and set aside.
Spray a 3-quart heavy saucepan with Pam. Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook and stir over medium heat using a candy thermometer.
Cook to 234°.
Stir constantly to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butterscotch chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Stir until melted. Stir in 1 cup of the pecans. Pour into pan, spreading evenly.
If desired, while fudge is still warm, sprinkle the remaining nuts and butterscotch chips onto the top and press gently.
Put into the refrigerator to chill.
Remove fudge and foil from the pan and cut into squares. Makes 4 1/2 pounds.
Very good.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil ham and water for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook until tender.
Blend in shaker the milk, cream and flour; then add to mixture.
Add Swiss and sharp cheese, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add more milk, if needed.

title: garlic pesto sauce
directions: Put in blender.
Puree.
After pasta is cooked, use a few spoonfuls of the pasta water to dilute the blended ingredients. Pour over and mix into pasta.
Serve with tossed green salad, bread sticks or garlic bread and salami.
Serves 4.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and add 1 stick of butter while hot. Shred cheese.
Mash potatoes and add cheese while hot.
Cook diced onions in butter.
Using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer bow ties, mashed potatoes and onion-butter mixture.
Repeat, ending with bow ties.
Pour remaining butter and onions over all.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until heated.

title: choffies(italian bows)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead 10 minutes; rub oil on outside of dough.
Roll very thin.
Cut in strips.
Fry.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Shake chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Brown chicken, then cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove a little of the juice to mix with sour cream.
Remove chicken and add sour cream.
If more gravy is desired, add milk.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, egg and butter.
Blend in bananas and milk. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: vegetable paella
directions: In a flat bottomed pan (at least 6-quart capacity), saute onions in oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, leeks, artichoke halves with juice, peppers, asparagus and peas.
Add 1 cup stock. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Blend in garlic, parsley and 3 1/2 cups stock.
In remaining cup of broth, boil saffron until bright orange in color (about 1 minute).
Add to pan.
Add rice and cook over medium heat, 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is done and liquid has evaporated.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In medium bowl combine flour and brown sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat with mixer until well blended.
Roll in a ball.
Roll in walnuts.
Chill.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Prepare chocolate crumb crust and set aside.
Heat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add melted chips and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water. Gradually add flour.
Blend in pecans.
Chill 4 hours.

title: graham cracker salad
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/3 cup for topping. Press other into oblong baking dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Stir in pineapple syrup.
Chill to partially set.
Add sour cream and vanilla and whip until fluffy.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle top with rest of crumbs.
Chill until firm.
Serve in squares.

title: grandma virginia's toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix well; add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Spread on greased 10x15 inch sided baking sheet.
You may have to wet your hand to press dough on sheet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise, and cheese.
Mix well.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until set (about 30 minutes).

title: classic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda together in bowl.
Cream margarine, sugars, vanilla, pudding and eggs.
Add flour mixture, then chips and nuts if desired.
Bake at 375°, 9 to 9 1/2 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: frankfurter scallop(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut half of the frankfurters into bite size pieces.
Combine soup, sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Mix well.
Add potatoes and franks.
Mix well.
Place in a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch casserole.

title: whipped pecan pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar, egg whites and vanilla; beat until stiff. Mix crackers, sugar and pecans.
Mix all together, stirring well. Place in a buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Let cool. Cover top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon butter layers
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with lemon

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, onion, garlic salt and oregano; simmer.
Cook noodles and drain. Pour 2/3 c. milk in noodles.
Layer in a casserole dish, noodles, meat and cheese; ending with cheese on top.
Put in moderate oven until cheese melts.
Makes
3 1/2 servings.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and flour until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each egg.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Place one wafer on the bottom of each cupcake holder.
Fill halfway up with mixture.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool and add topping of your choice.

title: lazy ladies
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add in order spreading evenly the graham crackers, nuts, chocolate chips and coconut. Do not mix or stir.
Pour evenly over all these layers of goodies the Eagle Brand milk (no other kind of milk will do). Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: honey baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Place in baking dish and dot each with butter. Spoon honey and cream evenly onto each apple.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour 1/4 cup water into bottom of baking pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 6. Can serve with ice cream or top with whipped cream.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat well at medium speed of mixer.
Combine banana, oats and milk; add to sugar mixture; beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into dry cup level with knife.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir with a whisk.
Add to sugar mixture.
Beat just until moist.
Spoon batter into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fruit compote
directions: Simmer any combination of dried fruit, such as apples, pears, raisins, peaches and apricots in enough water to cover.
Add water as needed during cooking, until all fruit is soft and tender.
Add sugar to taste and about a 1-inch stick of cinnamon; add a strip of lemon rind.
If cinnamon is unavailable, a pinch of ground cinnamon may be used.
May be served hot or cold, as preferred.

title: beef wellington
directions: Tie ends of fillet into place with cord.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and brush on beef.
Roast at 400° for about 10 minutes (rare), 15 minutes (medium) and 20 (well).
Remove and cool on rack.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in very large skillet. Drain.
Add tomatoes (break up with fork).
Add tomato paste and spices.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Make layers of noodles, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Crush cornflakes to one cup; pour in large bowl.
Add egg, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add meat; mix.
Shape into 6 loaves, about 4 inches long.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove; top each loaf with half a slice of cheese.
Return to oven; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: glazed almond cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, flavorings and egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat until light.
Add nuts, flour and salt; mix well. Chill, then roll into balls, about 1 inch round, dip in unbeaten egg whites and bake on greased sheets, putting 1 almond in depressed center of each ball.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, butter, sugar, oats, vanilla and cocoa.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell arranged in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: jello cottage cheese delight
directions: Fold all together with dry jello and serve.

title: creamy topped chocolate pie
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill one hour.

title: harriett's fresh fruit pie
directions: In saucepan, mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch.
Gradually stir in the orange juice until smooth.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1/4 cup lemon juice; cool completely.
Fold in the cut up fresh fruit.
Turn into baked cookie crust.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: fresh tomato sandwich
directions: Spread 2 slices of bread with mayonnaise.
Top with thin slices of Vidalia onion.
Cover onion with ripe tomato slices. Drizzle tomato slices with olive oil and season with salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste.
Slice into halves and serve.

title: pumpkin or squash pie (sweet potato)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells or into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1/2 way between center and edge comes out clean.

title: petite ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Arrange evenly in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Combine deviled ham and butter.
Mix well.
Spread on biscuit pieces.
Spoon cheese on top.
Sprinkle lightly with lemon pepper.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yields 40.

title: world's best brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease 10 x 14-inch pan.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler until melted.
Pour over chocolate chips and add remainder of cake mixture by teaspoonful over top of caramel mixture.
Bake 18 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour and cut into squares.

title: mystery salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium sized serving bowl. Sprinkle more chopped walnuts on top.
Cover and refrigerate. Serves 8 to 10.

title: nutty funnel cakes
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Position knife blade in food processor bowl. Add pecans; process until finely chopped. Add flour and next 4 ingredients; cover with lid and process 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth.

title: herb and chicken casserole
directions: Stew the chicken and remove from bones.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the broth. Cube or chop chicken and place in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix soups with milk and pour over chicken.
Melt butter and mix with broth.
Mix this with stuffing.
Place on top of soup and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread soft ice cream over crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.
Mix powdered sugar, milk, chips and 1/2 cup butter.
Boil for 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream and freeze.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: grape jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: apache bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll out about 1/2-inch thick and cut into squares. Fry in deep fat fryer in oil at least 2-inches deep, turning until golden brown on both sides.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk with enough orange drink to fill freezer can.
Freeze according to directions with freezer.

title: courting dip (shrimp #3)
directions: After pulverizing shrimp, mix with first 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Add garlic and second 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with potato chips.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Pre heat oven 350 degrees. Drain about 1/3 juice from pineapple, mix pineapple and cheese together, set aside. Mix sugar and flour; add to first mixture. Spread mixture in 9 X 13 casserole pan. Spread crushed crackers over top. Pour melted butter over all. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Let cook and serve. (This dish is good hot or cold, so leftovers, if you are so lucky are a snap.)

title: glorified rice
directions: Add
butter and sugar to rice.	Combine with pineapple, chopped apple
and marshmallows.
Let stand one hour.
Fold in Cool Whip.	Serves 6.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Cut up onion and celery; puree in food processor.
Heat margarine to bubbling hot in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add celery and onion mixture.
Reduce heat to medium; cook until thoroughly softened, but not browned.
Add flour; stir together to form a smooth paste.
Reduce heat to low; cook for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Slowly add chicken base and water, whipping constantly to ensure smoothness.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Lower heat; cook for 1 hour.
Add half and half; blend well.
Add chicken meat and salt and pepper to taste; simmer for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange jello, cottage cheese and fruits together.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well, then stir.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add molasses and unbeaten egg.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with vinegar and water.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet or add enough flour to roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: mom's cookie press cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, making sure they are mixed well. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in several drops of colored food coloring if desired.
Using the cookie press and any shape, press cookies onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges start to golden.
Watch first batch, as you may be able to bake less.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together vinegar, brown sugar, onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and water; set aside.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, milk and 3/4 cup of mixture together.
Form into meatballs and place in dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: french casserole
directions: Start cooking beans, add quartered carrots, chicken broth, bay leaves, onion, salt, pepper, garlic, thyme, marjoram and sage.
Add tomatoes and sausage.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Add all to covered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes.
Then uncover and bake 10 minutes more at 350°.
`If too dry add more chicken broth.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients;
cook in well greased 8-inch iron skillet at 400° about 35 minutes.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half length-wise.
Scoop out seeds.
Turn cut-side down into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add about a cup of water to pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Turn squash halves face up.
Divide remaining ingredients evenly between the 2 hollows.
Return to oven.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more or until squash is very tender.
(Be careful not to pierce skin.)
Lift out of pan and onto serving platter.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in small amount of oleo.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Serve hot from chafing dish with corn chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and add carrots and pecans.
Blend well.
Pour into greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: mushroom onion soup
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
In a large saucepan, melt butter; add mushrooms and onions.
Cook and stir over low heat for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, add broth, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Reduce heat.
Add rice and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until the rice is tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 servings (about 1 1/2 quarts).

title: stove top tamale pie
directions: In a Dutch oven, fry ground chuck and onion until meat is cooked through.
Add tomatoes, creamed corn, milk, cornmeal, salt, chili powder and olives; mix well.
Cover with 1/8-inch (or more) thick strips of Jack cheese.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes on top of the stove on low heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken; set aside.
Cook and drain spaghetti. Add all ingredients together; cook for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt in saucepan 1 stick of margarine.
Add 1 cup of crushed pretzels and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: chow fun
directions: Heat oil in skillet until very hot.
Fry char siu for 1 minute. Add next 4 ingredients.
Cook 1 minute.
Add vegetables.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add drained noodles.
Cook 2 minutes.
Put into shallow bowl.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until brown.
Stir to crumble.
Drain off any grease.
Spoon into 8 or 9-inch pan.
Add pizza
sauce. Place pepperoni slices on top of pizza sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: spinach squares
directions: Cook
spinach
and
drain.
Melt
butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients and place in pan.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple-ham deep dish pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Blend in flour, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until very thick.
In a 1-quart deep baking dish, combine ham and apples.
Sprinkle with cheese; pour sauce over top. Top with crust and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or top with mashed potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in large Ziploc bag using rolling pin or food processor.
Cream together the butter, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.

title: ooma's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup sugar well; add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When starts to thicken, add beaten egg yolks.
Continue cooking and stirring until very thick.
Cool.
In pan, alternate bananas, wafers and pudding in layers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until peaks form.
Top pudding and bake in 350° oven until brown on peaks.

title: taco pie
directions: Press rolls into pie plate.
Brown turkey in skillet.
Add bouillon, onion and pepper.
Add water, tomato paste and seasoning mix.
Cook until water is evaporated.
Put 1/2 of turkey mix into crust.
Top with 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raggmunkar(small potato pancakes for 4 persons)
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add half of the milk and whip it into a batter, free of lumps.
Add the rest of the milk and the egg. Peel the potatoes and shred them (a food processor works fine). Mix the shredded potatoes into the batter immediately, so that they don't turn gray.
Let some margarine or butter melt and turn light brown in a frying pan.
Fry the batter as pancakes (not quite 1 dl (1/3 cup) batter per pancake).
Serve the Raggmunkar directly from the pan with crisp fried bacon, lingonberry jam and shredded carrots.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce, dash of sugar and dash of salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Boil curly noodles.
Drain and add sour cream.
Layer noodles and meat sauce.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Spread lettuce in 9 x 12 inch dish and add the next 5 ingredients in layers. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar, and spread over mixture, being certain to cover completely to the edges. Top with shredded cheese and bacon. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil all ingredients except jello, until semi thick. Remove from heat. Add jello. Slice strawberries into baked pie shell. Pour mixture over strawberries and refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Top with dollop of whipped cream.

title: ranch beans
directions: Drain the butter beans and kidney beans. Add the pork and beans.
Mix together with the other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candy cane cafe beef enchiladas
directions: Mix tomato paste, water and enchilada sauce mix in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: smoked sausages
directions: Cut bacon slices in half and wrap each sausage.
Insert toothpick to hold bacon.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bacon is brown.

title: quick chowder (soup)
directions: Melt margarine.
Brown onions and ham.
Blend in soup, milk, corn and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish in layers:
pineapple, pie filling, cake mix and nuts.
Cut margarine over top.
Cook at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: "make your own stickers" sticker glue
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil.
Add gelatine; reduce heat to low. Stir until gelatine dissolves.
Add flavoring.
To use, brush on the back of "sticker" and let dry.
Great for rainy day lickin' and stickin'!

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven, about 15 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder 3 times and set aside. Cream the butter and Crisco thoroughly. Add sugar.
Cream well. Put vanilla and lemon flavoring in the milk. Add 1/2 milk to mixture, then add a little flour and one egg.
Repeat until all flour and eggs are used, beating well. Add remaining milk, still beating until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours for tube pan. (Less time needed for 2 loaf pans.)

title: italian delight
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together; drain off fat.
Add soups and corn.
Heat thoroughly.
Then add noodles and cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla thoroughly; add eggs, one at at time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder; add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Cookies will be soft.

title: spam sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add mayonnaise to taste.
Spread on bread.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Stir in milk.
Spread in prepared dish.
Spoon apples onto batter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Batter will rise to top.
May substitute favorite canned or fresh fruit for apples.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix flour, meal, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add egg.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Add milk and stir only until moistened. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in Spry.
Add milk, mixing to a soft dough.
Knead lightly 20 seconds.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add water to egg white and stir. Add pecan halves. Mix dry ingredients and put in large zip lock bag. Add pecans and shake well. Put on greased cookie sheet (pan with sides). Bake at 300° for 20-21 minutes. Stir twice.

title: toasted almond swiss spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and spread in a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake 15 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Garnish with more almonds.
Serve on crackers or toast points.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream, and taco seasoning mix. Spread in the bottom of a pie plate.
On top of this mixture layer lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives, and onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot pickles
directions: Mix in a large container until sugar dissolves.
Put back into a gallon jar.
Refrigerate.

title: louise's chinese salad
directions: Boil chicken and shred.
Deep fry rice sticks.
Shred lettuce. Chop onions.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and serve with dressing made from remaining ingredients.

title: dreamy fruit salad
directions: Add about 4 to 5 drops of red food coloring to sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, then remainder of ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix cream of broccoli soup and water together.
Grease a pan. Put the 6 half breasts of chicken with cheese over it in pan.
(I use 1/2 slice of American on each.)
Pour mix of soup and water over chicken.
Toss bread stuffing over chicken and liquids.
Add 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, except for last 15 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: baked green peppers
directions: Cut each pepper into quarters; remove seeds and fibrous portions. Put into baking pan with oil and garlic and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Serves 6.

title: pluck-it cake
directions: Generously grease Bundt pan.
In plastic bag put mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits, one can at a time, into quarters and shake in plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon to coat.
Place these pieces in Bundt pan.
Melt 15 tablespoons butter; mix in white and brown sugars and heat until melted.
Pour 1/4 of this mixture over first can of biscuits.
Repeat this procedure, alternating sugar and butter mixture and biscuit quarters until gone.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn pan over onto plate as soon as removed from oven.
Do not remove pan for 15 minutes. Serve warm or cold.
Just "pluck" off a piece with your fingers.

title: peanut butter cookies(no bake)
directions: Heat syrup and sugar together until well melted.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and noodles; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, grated rind and sugar.
Cool until it begins to jell.

title: potato salad
directions: Mash egg yolks.
Add mustard, milk, sugar, salad dressing, salt and vinegar.
Mix well. Pour over potatoes, onions, etc.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in 3 pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bonnie's pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and seasonings in clear jars.
Boil brine ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Seal and 10 minute hot water bath.

title: squash relish
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes and add to mixture.
Bring to boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Put in jars.
Makes about 4 to 5 pints.

title: easy chili dip
directions: Chop peppers and onion into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
