Heat just until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips and enjoy!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
May bake in a loaf pan or casserole dish.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: (You can use 1 cup sweet milk and 1 teaspoon vinegar as substitute for sour milk.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, fry hamburger meat until no longer pink. Add onions and pepper and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve on hamburger buns (optional: with slices of onions).

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Put 1 cup coconut in bottom of crust.
Put pineapple on coconut.
Pour custard on pineapple.
Bake at 350°.
Beat egg whites and decorate with pineapple and coconut.
Brown in oven until light brown.

title: million dollar rice
directions: Blend together and fold into first mixture and chill before serving.

title: mary's orange things
directions: Blend vanilla wafers, melted butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well, adding thawed orange juice undiluted last.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll in balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
May need re-rolling in powdered sugar prior to serving.
One box vanilla wafers = 49 (1-inch) balls.
Two boxes vanilla wafers = 98 (1-inch) balls.
Party food.

title: apricot delight
directions: Place vanilla wafers in a well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook in double boiler eggs, oleo and powdered sugar until it is the consistency of mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Let cool. Put nuts over the filling.
Put Cool Whip over filling.
Pour baby food over top of Cool Whip.
Let set 24 to 48 hours before serving.

title: white cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, add flour, baking powder, water and flavorings.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites, fold them in lightly.
Bake at 350°.
Put the batter in a large angel cake pan for a birthday cake.
It is lovely used for a brides cake.
May use lemon flavoring.

title: oven-fried herbed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow bowl blend together bread crumbs, (plain salad croutons crushed make a good substitute for dry bread) Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan heat butter and garlic over a low heat until butter is melted and let simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and dip chicken pieces in butter, then dredge in crumb mixture.
Place chicken on foil lined baking pan and sprinkle any remaining crumbs and butter over all. Bake uncovered 45 minutes until done and well browned.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: In saucepan, melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry cake mix, melted butter, remaining 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Pat 1/2 of this mixture into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes

title: pesto sauce
directions: In a blender jar, mix olive oil, water, basil and garlic. Blend on high speed.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add pepper, salt and pine nuts.
Blend at a lower speed.
Add parsley and cheese. Mix again.
Serve pesto over pasta.

title: spinach, fennel and pink grapefruit salad
directions: In blender, mix vinegar, grapefruit juice, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Add the oil and blend until it is emulsified. Arrange spinach on salad plates, then top with grapefruit segments and fennel slices (that have been drained).
Drizzle with dressing.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place unopened cans of milk in stockpot.
Completely cover with water (covered at all times with water).

Boil for 3 hours. Take out of pan with pot holders (very very hot). Cover cans with paper towels, then poke hole in cans to let out steam. Open cans and empty into pie shell. Let cool, then put Cool Whip on top. Grate chocolate on top if you like.

title: homemade miracle whip
directions: To make sawmill gravy, use the bacon drippings or fried ham grease left in the skillet after frying the meat and taking it out. Add flour to the hot grease and let it brown slightly.
Thin the mixture a little with water, then add milk and salt and pepper. Stir and cook until fairly thick.
Great with Cat Head Biscuits.

title: joyce's shrimp fondue
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
When cheese is melted, place in fondue pot.
Add shrimp and pimientos.
Chop tomatoes and add or delete as desired.
Keep warm and serve with cubed bread.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake in cupcake pans and grease bottoms only.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until the flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffins about 3/4 full.
When baked, remove immediately from pan.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: lime surprise salad
directions: Mix the 2 gelatins with hot water.
Let cool.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add to gelatin; mix and refrigerate.

title: cabin relish
directions: Chop maters, pepper, onion and cucumber.
Mix in vinegah 'n chill in ice box fore usin'.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons of the cocoa.
Stir in the milk, oil and pecans. Spread the mixture into a greased 9-inch deep dish pie plate.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
After mixing, make 3 holes (wells).
Add vinegar in one, cooking oil in another and water in the last.
Mix together well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch or 2 (8-inch) round greased pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Leave plain, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or use your favorite icing.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly on bottom of pan.

title: crab salad
directions: Dice bread, eggs, and onion, mix together and refrigerate. Add remaining ingredients and mix together.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually and then add salt and vanilla.
Continue beating while adding cream and half and half.
Add fruit.

title: richard's german chicken corn soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove from pan and skin and de-bone the leg and thigh
quarters.
To broth, add rest of the ingredients and cook until potatoes are semi-soft. Add chicken and heat through.
This is a wonderful hearty soup. It freezes well and tastes great.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill the dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chinese style rice
directions: Scramble egg in oil in saucepan, stirring to break into small pieces.
Add water, soy sauce, garlic powder and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork before serving.
Makes 2 cups.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until melted.
Place Rice Chex in large bowl; pour mixture over and mix well.
Put powdered sugar in a big grocery bag; add Chex mixture and shake.
Put on waxed paper to dry, about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: my sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Work butter until fluffy, add sugar and yolk, mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour milk and vanilla.
Mix well, fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar and nutmeg mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 18 cookies.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry) with corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in a small mixer bowl.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form (about 5 minutes).
Transfer to a large mixer bowl.
On low speed, gradually blend in powdered sugar.
Stir in nuts by hand.

title: brownies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt margarine and chocolate.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add to chocolate and margarine.
Add flour; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on serving dish.
Drain crabmeat, flake over cream cheese, pushing meat into cheese.
Spread chili sauce over crabmeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: peppered pork
directions: Roll pork tenderloins in pepper to coat; place in roasting pan. Roast in a preheated 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes until cooked through.
Pour fat off pan.
Add wine.
Place pan on burner over high heat.
Cook, scraping up browned bits, 1 minute.
Add broth. Cook, stirring to reduce liquid by half 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine sour cream and mustard.
Stir into pan.
Slice pork. Serve with sauce.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes, unwrapped, at 450° for about 1 1/4 hours, or until well done.
Grate cheese in a large bowl; reserve about 1/4 of cheese for top.
Grate onion.
Add margarine.
Split potatoes when done lengthwise; dip out potato meat.
Mix well with cheese mixture, using electric mixer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dip back into shells.
Sprinkle reserved cheese on top; bake until cheese melts and lightly browns.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake in casserole dish at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice to mix with pudding mix. Combine frozen fruits, pineapple and bananas.
Mix thoroughly with the pudding mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: broccoli-grape salad
directions: Combine broccoli, grapes, almonds and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Toss and chill.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small bowl with electric mixer, combine cheese, margarine and vanilla and beat on low speed.
Gradually add sugar continuing beating on medium speed until fluffy.

title: quickie pineapple spam-luncheon meat
directions: Pour
sauce
over
Spam;
simmer
for 15 to 20 minutes. (May be baked at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.)

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, corn syrup, eggs, melted butter and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Stir in pecans; pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
For best flavor, cover and let stand 1 day before serving.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.

title: air-dry clay
directions: Cut with cookie cutters or mold into shapes.
Let dry overnight and paint.

title: chicken cornbread casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mash cornbread. Add butter and sage. Spread 1/2 cornbread in a buttered casserole.
Cover with chopped chicken.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over top of chicken.
Add rest of cornbread mixture.
Pour broth over all. Should be very moist.
Add more broth, if needed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ma belks' tea cakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Cut grapefruit rinds into strips; cover in cold water and boil 2 minutes.
Repeat this procedure 3 times; drain thoroughly.
Make syrup of sugar and water; bring to boil and put in the rinds. Boil slowly until all syrup is absorbed.
Spread on cookie sheet and drop each piece of rind in granulated sugar and leave spread out until dry.

title: frozen strawberry whip
directions: Make jello (1 cup cold and 1 cup hot water), chill until jelly consistency.
Cream Philadelphia cream cheese with mixer.
Add sugar, chop strawberries and add to sugar and cheese.
Add Cool Whip, then add jello.
Beat together.
Place in a glass flat dish, chill overnight.
Can garnish with strawberries.
Cut into squares.

title: cabbage casserole #1
directions: Cook meat and onion in saucepan.
Cut up cabbage and add to meat mixture.
Cook until cabbage is done.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: favorite potato salad(4 to 5 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes just until tender.
As soon as you can handle them, peel and slice potatoes.
Immediately sprinkle with salt, sugar, celery seed and vinegar.
Toss until all potatoes are seasoned.
Add onion and 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Toss until well distributed.
With rubber spatula, fold in mayonnaise, celery and sliced eggs until well mixed.
Add remainder or mayonnaise, if necessary.
Chill.

title: cajun swiss steak
directions: Pound meat; season with salt and cayenne pepper.
Dust with flour.
In heavy iron skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Remove and set aside.
Add all vegetables and saute until limp (about 5 minutes).
Add water.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to simmer. Add bay leaf.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in 3 greased loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Chill and serve with bread squares or crackers.

title: cold fudge
directions: Put in bowl to have ready the chocolate chips, German chocolate, Marshmallow Fluff, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together in large pot the sugar, butter and canned milk.
Bring to full boil. Stirring constantly, boil for 10 minutes; turn off heat.
Quickly put bowl mixture into pot and mix well.
Line pan in oil.
Pour and let cool, then refrigerate.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Brown chicken in oil.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in skillet with chicken.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix cocoa with sugar and mix the rest.
Cook until mixture will form a soft ball in cold water.
Beat until cool and spread on cake.

title: texas a.m. casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown crumbled sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over bread, then layer with cheese.
Combine mustard, cream and eggs; beat well.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix, reserving part of the cheese for top.
Can put buttered bread crumbs or crumbled corn flakes on top.
Bake until bubbly and brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: *French hard cheese is not easy to find.
Parmesan or Romano are fine.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. In a large mixing bowl, mix broccoli, mayonnaise, onion, soup and pecans, then mix in egg.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Then spread crumbs over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
In a separate bowl, work shortening, 1 1/4 cup sugar and eggs, one at a time, with spoon until soft.
Mix 1/2 cup cocoa, boiling water and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients. Bake in 2 layers at 350°.
Cool and split layers.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute slightly salted and peppered chicken pieces in butter and oil for 10 minutes.
Cook spinach, drain and squeeze dry.
Spread spinach in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with chicken.

title: ranch pasta primavera
directions: Steam carrots and broccoli until tender-crisp; cool.
Cook fettucine in chicken broth, just until tender; drain and cool. Combine vegetables and pasta.
Add basil to salad dressing; toss gently into pasta and vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper in margarine for a few minutes.
Do not brown.
Remove from fire.
Add soups, cheese, seasonings, rice and water.
Place in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with bread crumbs and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until rice is done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems, measure 1/2 cup.
Cook 1/2 of the stems with 3 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Repeat with remaining stems and butter.
Combine cream cheese and Blue cheese. Stir in stems and onions.
Place on baking sheet and bake until golden brown.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda in bowl and set aside. Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Pour in rice and brown.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: *Make with Cheddar cheese and milk; use cheese soup or Cheez Whiz.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, coarsely crush the crackers with your hands.
You should have big cracker pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well and serve immediately.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
EXCELLENT!
Yield:
6 servings.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: roger lane cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat egg yolks; add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Use 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer pans lined with wax paper, greased well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: triple layer salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple with Jell-O.
Chill until firm.
Combine remaining ingredients except water and lime Jell-O.
Spread on firm jello and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Pour over mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese pepper dish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Open pepper cans and drain. Split peppers and remove seeds and splines.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peeled potatoes boiled, tender, mash, whipped smooth.
Add ingredients.
Beat until fluffy, cool and cover and put in refrigerator.
Use within 2 weeks as needed.
To heat:
Dot with butter, bake covered casserole at 350°.
Heat through.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: "raisin puffs" cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water over low heat until dry.
Cool.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in raisins last.
Make into small balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook macaroni to package directions. Drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion flakes and garlic salt.
Gently fold in the cooked macaroni and place in a casserole dish.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: laura auman's german chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add soups plus pimentos and 1 cup water. Set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Beginning with hamburger mixture layer casserole dish:
hamburger, noodles and cheese, until all gone, topping with hamburger.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jel-juice-o
directions: Put agar-agar and 1/2 cup apple juice in saucepan.
Dissolve over heat and bring to a boil until agar looks clear.
Remove from heat, cool a little.
Add remaining juice.
Pour in mold and chill until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: smoky beef salami
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Divide mixture and roll into logs.
Wrap logs with nylon net or cheesecloth.
Bake in oven in broiler pan with rack at 225° for about 4 hours or at 150° for about 9 hours or at 140° for about 11 hours, or microwave about 1 hour at Defrost setting.
Turn occasionally while baking.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Note:
Drain the pineapple the night before.

title: delices de fromage(deep-fried cheese squares)
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter over moderate heat.
When the foam begins to subside, stir in 3/4 cup of the flour and mix together thoroughly.
Pour in the milk and stir constantly with a whisk.
Cook over high heat until the sauce comes to a boil and thickens.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, whisking frequently.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Using a wooden spoon, vigorously beat in the egg yolks, one at a time.
Add the salt and pepper and stir in the grated cheese.
When thoroughly combined, pour the mixture into a lightly buttered 8 x 6-inch baking dish, spreading it out to 1/2-inch thickness and smoothing the top.
Cool to room temperature, then cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or until firm.
With a pastry wheel or sharp knife, cut the cheese mixture into 2-inch squares, lifting them out of the dish with a small spatula and placing them on waxed paper.
Dip the squares in the remaining flour, one at a time. When they are completely coated on all sides, shake off any excess flour and dip them into the egg and milk mixture.
Coat them on all sides with the bread crumbs, patting gently with a spatula to make them adhere.
Arrange the squares on a large baking sheet and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, until the coating is firm.
Pour enough oil into a deep-fryer or large, heavy saucepan to come 2 to 3-inches up the sides of the pan and heat the oil until it reaches 375°.
Preheat oven to its lowest setting.
Line a large baking dish with a double thickness of paper towels and place it in the middle of the oven.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Put oil in a large frying pan. Combine beef, potatoes and onion.
Cook until slightly browned. Keep mixing to cook thoroughly.
Covering the pan is recommended.

title: shrimp-cream cheese cold pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on large glass plate or pizza pan.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Serve chilled with wheat crackers.

title: nanaw's pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place on foil lined pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes covered with foil; turn after the first 10 minutes.
After baking for 20 minutes; remove from oven.
Drain pan and add applesauce on top of each pork chop.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Return to oven uncovered until thoroughly heated.
Very quick and easy!

title: chicken soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add chicken and all of the other ingredients into pot.
Boil in a covered pan for 1 1/2 hours. Lower heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve soup in bowls.
Chicken can be deboned and added to soup or can be served separately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well with wire whip.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Decorate top of pie with pecan halves.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake about 30 minutes longer.

title: sue's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and Karo together.
Add sugar, margarine (chopped into small pieces), vanilla and pecans.
Stir well and pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken and corn casserole
directions: Line bottom and sides of heavily greased casserole with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Add alternate layers of corn and chicken, then add salt and pepper.
Mix the eggs and milk; pour over the chicken mixture.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs, cheese and butter. Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheddar cheese meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and drain.
May add onion or vegetable of your choice to add variety or color.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and let cool down.
Remove crescent rolls from can and gently pull away, leaving dough in 2 sections.
Gently finger dough to spread out into a square shape.
Place meat and cheese mixture on top of one of the dough squares.
Gently place the second dough square on top of meat mixture and press together the edges of the dough.
Follow the baking instructions on the crescent dinner roll can and bake until done.
Delicious!

title: ranch style dressing
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Serve over salad or raw vegetables.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Melt butter with cream cheese.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, water and salt over medium heat until the water is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, nutmeg, raisins and butter.
Mix well.
Put into a pan greased with butter.
Set pan in another pan half full of water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best of the west chili
directions: In skillet over medium heat, combine oil, peppers and onion and saute until vegetables are soft.
Add meat and simmer until brown.
In large crock-pot, add vinegar, beans, stewed tomatoes and salsa.
Heat on high and stir.
After simmering is done, transfer skillet mixture to crock-pot.
Season with beef bouillon cubes and cook on high 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: murgh ke shami
directions: Wash the boneless chicken and drain out excess moisture. Soak chana dal for at least three hours.
Chop the onions, coriander leaves, mint leaves and mix them with lemon juice to make a stuffing.
Divide into sixteen equal portions and keep aside.

title: ann's squash casserole
directions: Mix together cooked squash, onion, egg yolks, cheese, soup, sugar, salt, pepper and set aside.

title: shrimp log
directions: Mix well in a blender; form as a log.
Pour shrimp cocktail sauce over log.

title: canned snap beans
directions: Boil for 40 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Be sure to drain water off before you get ready to cook.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Bring sugar and butter to a boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients and drop onto wax paper.
Let harden before eating.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
May add other fruits such as strawberries and peaches.

title: dolly parton cabbage
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in a bit of oil or butter until tender.
Add cabbage and tomatoes and cook over medium heat until cabbage is tender.
Very low calorie.

title: beef n cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cook rice, salt and pepper.
Chop cabbage, put in bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 400° for the first 15 minutes and 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: peach or fruit cobbler(freezes!)
directions: Mix fruit with sugar.
Set aside.
Put butter in baking dish and set in a 350° oven to melt.
Make batter of 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over butter, but do not stir. Put sugared fruit on batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: In hot oil, saute onions until tender (use large kettle).
Add water, potatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add shrimp.
Heat milk and cheese ingredients until melted.
Add to shrimp with parsley.
Depending on the thickness you desire, you may want to add more or less milk.
Chicken may be substituted for shrimp.
Can be made in crock-pot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mash and add all ingredients.
Save a little cheese and sprinkle on top.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts. Chill.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat all in skillet.
Add crab and veggies.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Cook 1 minute more.
Serve over rice.
Serves 3.

title: nana's foolproof rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Turn out on floured board and knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut rolls into desired shape.
Place on lightly oiled cookie sheet and let rise about 15 minutes. Brush with egg white and a little water, mixed.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: chili
directions: Put hamburger in large	skillet
and
cook until brown. Then add other ingredients
and	simmer	until
well
blended. Serve while hot.	Makes a good meat served with crackers and a salad.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves about 6.
Excellent for summer.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Spread the cream cheese on pizza.
Cover with sauces.
Sprinkle with the peppers, onion, shrimp, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese. Serve with Doritos or tostados.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch together; bring to a boil and cook until thick and clear.
Add jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberries; stir to coat all the berries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sugar-free raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples in a bowl; set aside for a few minutes. Mix dry ingredients with apples.
Add eggs, applesauce, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: viennese coffee
directions: Place 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon in each of 4 dinner cups and fill with coffee. Stir.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugar, eggs, cinnamon and salt together to prevent potatoes from turning brown.
Grate them after mixing other ingredients.
Immediately add the grated potatoes to mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until crusty on top.
The casserole can be made the day before and kept in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: terri's breakfast surprise
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and then add the frozen (or thawed) hash browns.
Cook until tender.
With a spoon, make 5 or 6 wells. Lightly spray wells with a cooking oil.
Add 1 egg to each well (may scramble or leave whole).
Cover and let poach.
When eggs are nearly done, add crumbled bacon (or crumbled ham or sausage) and shredded cheese until melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash ingredients together to the consistency that you like. Serve cold with tortilla chips.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except the Velveeta in a food processor or blender.
Simmer 2 hours or more.
Add the cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve warm.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery with the meat.
Stir in roux, onion tops and parsley.
Add water and rice. Stir, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Mix all together.
May be lumpy.
Divide between 2 greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cuts best with electric knife.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir a moderate amount of hot mixture into yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Add 1 cup flaked coconut to vanilla cream pie filling.
Pour into cooled baked pastry shell*. Spread meringue atop pie.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Mix together the sweetened condensed milk and 1 cup of cold water; add vanilla pudding and beat for 3 minutes.
Put in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Tear cake into pieces and put half of cake in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat whipped cream; add sugar and vanilla to taste.
Add 2 cups whipped cream to milk mixture.
Fold together.
Put half of this on top of angel food cake, then put a layer of strawberries.
Then use the rest of the cake, another layer of cream mixture, layer of strawberries and then final layer of remaining whipped cream.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: mom's icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add beaten eggs and cream together. Add nuts. Sift flour, soda and salt and add to mixture slowly. Make into rolls and roll up in wax paper and chill overnight. Slice in thin slices and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Do not grease cookie sheet!!

title: country a b c cobbler
directions: Mix pie fillings, sugars, spices and margarine together.
Put one crust on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Pour in filling.
Cut remaining crust into strips; crisscross on top of cobbler.
Flute edges.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add to egg yolks.
Add milk and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
You can use 1 cup pecans and this makes a good pecan pie.

title: homemade graham crackers
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon into a bowl.
Melt together the butter and honey.
Pour this into the dry ingredients.
Mix with a fork.
Push the dough together with your hands.
Do not overmix nor knead.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in applesauce.
Pour into 4 1/2-cup ring mold. Chill until firm.

title: my daddy's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add cocoa and water to heat to boiling.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl and gradually add to cocoa mixture.
Sour milk with vinegar and add this, the eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Once you've eaten this, you'll never buy Betty Crocker again!

title: oven omelet
directions: Beat eggs, salt, paprika, mustard and milk together.
Add meat and pour over bread cubes in a greased pan.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15, depending on the size of serving.

title: penuche
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugars, cream, milk and butter or margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugars dissolve and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring only if necessary.
Immediately remove from heat and cool to lukewarm until candy becomes very thick and starts to lose its gloss. Quickly stir in nuts and spread in buttered shallow pan.
Score in squares while warm, cut when firm.

title: shaker pickles
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Do not heat.
Put cucumbers in gallon jar.
Pour liquid mixture over cucumbers.
Let set 3 to 4 days, shaking often.
Will keep in refrigerator indefinitely.
You can add onions for flavor.

title: soft sesame pretzels
directions: Start yeast growing, then mix yeast, honey and water.
Wait 5 to 10 minutes until foamy. While waiting, grate the cheese.
Mix flours and yeast until dough is smooth and can be easily stretched (5 to 10 minutes).
Mix in cheese.
Make 6 to 8 balls of mixture and roll into snake and shape into pretzel.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Beat the egg and brush on top.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brown, but still soft.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo, then add eggs.
Dredge chopped fruit with flour. Put soda in buttermilk and mix all together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until slightly brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: oven fried cinnamon chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Mix the salt, pepper and flour and spread on a plate.
In a small bowl, whisk the turmeric and cinnamon into the egg whites.
Dredge the chicken pieces in the flour, then dip them in the egg whites and coat them with the bread crumbs.

title: pistoletts(these are delicious)
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain off any fat).
Add cheese and broccoli (which has been cooked and drained thoroughly).
Cut off tip end of each roll (one at a time).
Remove the inside and spoon mixture into roll.
Replace the end you just cut off.
Roll in garlic butter and bake until brown.
Do not overbake.
These can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: hamburger sausage dip
directions: Combine sausage, hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until well done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve in fondue pot or chafing dish.

title: no bake cake
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly on bottom of a large oblong pan.
Pour pineapple evenly over cake.
Heat milk and marshmallows in a saucepan over low heat until marshmallows are dissolved. Pour evenly over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle coconut.
Chill.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high with electric mixer about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.

title: chocolate p-nut butter balls
directions: Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl; mix well. Roll into bite-sized balls.
Place on waxed paper.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, dill, cucumber and dressing until well combined.
Top each toast slice with 1/2 cup tuna mixture, 1 slice tomato and 1 slice cheese.
Broil in preheated broiler 6-inches from heat until cheese melts.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: grandma sara's michigan pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Add flour and sweet cream, a little at a time, ending with flour; mix well.
Pour mixture into a large tube pan.
Spray pan with Baker's Choice.
Bake at 275° until done (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat ingredients together until sugar dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Place hard-boiled eggs in gallon jar; pour syrup over. Refrigerate.
Reduce recipe if you only want to make enough eggs for a quart jar.

title: old fashioned bakewell cream biscuits
directions: This amount makes 24 biscuits, but you may halve it easily. Mix and sift first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening and cut in, using pastry blender or 2 knives.
Use a vegetable shortening for these biscuits.
Add milk all at once, stir quickly with a fork to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead 5 to 6 times. Roll out 1/2 inch or more thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with a little butter or milk. Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and continue to bake on stored heat until golden brown.

title: sauce sabayon with raspberries
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients over a double boiler, making sure not to scramble the eggs.
When the mixture is thick and creamy, serve over the fresh fruit or even plain with a little sherry drizzled into each serving.

title: orange sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; blend into butter. Stir in orange juice and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: watergate salad(great)
directions: Mix yogurt and fruit first.
Put pudding and sweetener.
Makes 4 servings.
Refrigerate.
One serving equals 1 milk and 1 fruit.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix until all is moistened. Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 5 to 10 times. Put out to a thickness of about 1/2 to 3/4-inch.
Cut and bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown. Enjoy buttered up or with chocolate gravy.

title: broccoli rice chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy, but good chicken
directions: Mix the soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour over breasts placed in flat baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for over 1 hour.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in a gallon container.
Add pineapple juice.
Add water to fill container.
Pour over crushed ice.
Add ginger ale (approximately 1 pint ginger ale) per punch bowl. Serve.

title: greek vegetable salad
directions: Steam beans until crisp-tender.
Combine the cabbage and Feta cheese in a bowl.
Mix the olive oil, vinegar and thyme in a small bowl.
When beans are done, refresh them in cold water until cooled.
Add to cabbage mixture and toss with dressing.
Serves 4.

title: steve's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins; mix thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil and let cool.
Pack jar with thin sliced onions and cucumbers tightly.
Pour liquid over and keep in refrigerator.
Let stand 1 month and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: walnut balls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Work in butter, at room temperature and vanilla.
Add 2 cups nuts, mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining nuts.
Bake on ungreased sheets 25 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: orzo casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine onion soup mix with water; set aside.
In saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Cook garlic with orzo, stirring constantly, until golden.
Stir in onion soup mix.
Bring to boil.
Simmer covered 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Do not stir.
Simmer covered 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Put in casserole dish.
Let stand 10 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

title: salsa
directions: Scald tomatoes and skin them.
Combine all ingredients; simmer for
hours.
The
last 10 minutes, add allspice and cinnamon. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: spinach beef roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into 4 rectangles.
Pound to 1/8-inch thickness. Mix spinach, carrot, cheese, oregano and pepper.
Spread over meat.
Roll up jelly-roll style.
Secure with wooden picks.
Brown meat in a Pam-sprayed skillet.
Add onion, garlic, tomato sauce, water, bouillon, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Transfer rolls to serving platter; discard picks and keep meat warm.
Stir cornstarch into 1/3 cup cold water; stir into pan juices.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Spoon sauce over rolls.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 8 to 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Brush with egg yolk.
Cool.
Layer with cheese, chicken and egg mixture. Repeat until all is used.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cup ice cream
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a blender.
Slowly add ice cream.
Mix well until well blended.
Pour into serving glasses. Add peanut butter cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an ungreased 8 x 12 inch casserole dish.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion in skillet until lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles according to directions. Drain noodles and can of corn.
Mix hamburger, noodles, sour cream, corn, soup, salt and pepper together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook on 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove; add cheese on top. Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and blend well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add vanilla to creamed mixture, then blend in the dry ingredients.
Fold in the apples and nuts to the other mixture. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach of a blueberry pie
directions: Combine the 1/3 cup flour, confectioners sugar, blueberries and peaches and place in the pie crust.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: louise's trifle
directions: The amount of each ingredient depends on size of container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix real well and let set for 2 hours before eating with chips.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; slice thin.
Make white sauce of margarine, flour and milk.
Put half of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole dish; cover with half of sauce, seasonings and onion.
Add remaining potatoes, seasonings and onion, then remaining sauce. Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until top is browned.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Place artichokes in bottom of baking dish.
Spread a layer of crab meat.
Add a layer of sauteed mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan; add remaining ingredients except cheese, stirring well after each addition to form a smooth sauce.
Pour over artichoke-crab-mushroom layers and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in a marinade container.
Let meat marinate overnight or at least 12 hours.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients, then put into containers to freeze.
When needed, shave off in the form of slush and add Sprite or 7-Up to glass.
Use 2/3 slush to 1/3 cup of pop.

title: golden bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs, Wesson oil and vanilla flavoring together with mixer.
Add flour and stir.
Then put in coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well with spoon.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes; do not open oven until time.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Pour apple cider into small pan; add cinnamon sticks and lemon juice.
Simmer gently 1/2 hour.
Put nutmeg and cloves into a cheesecloth bag and drop into apple cider for a period suitable to your taste.
Serves 8.

title: pecan roll(no bake)
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Knead until all sugar is thoroughly blended.
Shape into 8 rolls.
Wrap each in plastic and freeze.
Melt caramels and heavy cream.
Dip frozen candy rolls in melted caramels and roll in chopped pecans.
Store covered in a cool dry place.

title: simple pumpkin bread
directions: Strain all liquid from pumpkin.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir all remaining ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes or until loaf tests done.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until soft ball stage.
Add other ingredients and whip together.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.

title: fresh apple pudding cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and egg.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: ritz bits snacks
directions: Set oven at 250°.
Mix dill weed, Ranch powder and oil thoroughly.
Pour Ritz Bits (dry) in lasagna pan.
Pour dressing over the crackers and mix carefully.
Spread out in pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake for another 10 minutes.
Cool and then place in a covered container.

title: guacamole (avocado) dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice and a few drops of hot pepper sauce to avocados.
Layer avocados, sour cream, taco sauce, cheese and scallions (one layer of each).
Serve with tortilla or Tostitos chips.

title: edith's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Sift and measure flour, then add salt, soda and baking powder and sift again.
Add flour mixture to creamed ingredients.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Roll dough in walnut size balls.
Place on baking sheet and press down with fork.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter in food processor until crumbly.
Core and peel apples.
With a fork, scratch the sides of the apples on all sides and roll in the crumb mixture, packing as much as possible on the sides.
Place the apples in a greased baking dish.

title: smoky tater casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and onion in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Add corn, green pepper, milk and pepper; stir until mixed.
Add sausage pieces, mixing lightly.
Cover.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes about 6 servings, 325 calories each.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and blend 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (or until knife inserted comes out clean).
The crust bakes down and the custard up.

title: cherry turnover bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and vanilla, then mix flour with baking powder.
Put 2/3 of the batter in a 12 x 15-inch bar pan and cover with 1 can cherry pie filling mixed with 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Drop
remaining 1/3 batter by teaspoons on top of cherry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frosting is optional.

title: party potatoes
directions: Whip all ingredients together as you would mashed potatoes. Top with grated Parmesan cheese and butter.
Can be made up to 2 days before serving. They taste
better because the flavors have time to marry.

title: korean steak
directions: Cut round steak into thin serving pieces and trim.
Combine other ingredients.
Marinate meat all day or overnight and then grill to your preference.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Roll dates, candy and nuts in 1/2 c. flour. Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and buttermilk. Sift flour and soda and fold in candy mixture. Add coconut. Pour into floured tube pan. Bake for 3 hours at 250 degrees. Glaze while hot.

title: orange-glazed chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Mix flour and barbecue sauce; add other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Baste while cooking with sauce.
May serve with cooked rice.

title: sausage, peppers and potatoes
directions: In 12 inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat and brown sausage.
Remove sausage and cut in 1 inch chunks and set aside. Reserve drippings.
Add green peppers to drippings.
Cook about 2 minutes stirring frequently.
Add potatoes and onion soup mix. Stir in water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with hot crusty Italian bread.
Serves 4.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Fill a 4-quart pot with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer breasts for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken; bone and cut into pieces. Strain broth and keep.
Add remaining ingredients to broth.
Add chicken meat.
Simmer 1 hour until vegetables are tender.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except shortening.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Make patties as a hamburger with the potato mixture.
Brown on both sides in a skillet with shortening.

title: chicken and rice(working mom's favorite)
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 can French fried onions and Italian seasoning in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour chicken broth over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken on top and pour salad dressing over chicken.

title: mexican stack
directions: Mix, brown and crumble the two meats.
Drain well.
Add chopped chilies and Velveeta.
Cook until melted.
Spread a flour tortilla with mixture.
Cover with another tortilla.
Repeat layers until you use 10 to 12 tortillas.
Serve in slices.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Pour over cabbage.
Cool and refrigerate.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain beef, bacon and onion.
Add beans and combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter in skillet until tender, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Add rice and saute for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bouillon, salt and raisins.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds and parsley.
Fluff with a fork.
Serves four.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla. Pour into a greased baking dish. Cover with topping and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: black beans with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Mix all ingredients, except salsa.
Pour into baking dish; bake for 20 minutes, or until golden, at 350°.
Serve with salsa.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and cap strawberries and slice.
Add sugar and let stand until juicy.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut ham and cheese into small pieces.
Slice chicken breasts down one side to form a deep pocket.
Stuff chicken as full as possible, sealing edges with skewers or toothpicks.
Mix flour, bread crumbs, paprika and pepper.
Coat breasts.
Brown chicken in butter.
When browned, add wine and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel peaches and slice.
Line in an unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Pour over peeled peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Put small amount of Crisco on pizza pan.
Spread cookie dough on pan with your hands.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't let it get too brown.
Cool for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce and seasoning; simmer 2 hours.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam, layer meat, then noodles.
Next to last, layer or spread on cottage cheese. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° until Mozzarella cheese melts and is lightly brown.

title: milky way cake
directions: In top of double boiler, melt Milky Way bars and margarine. Set this aside to cool. Mix the Crisco and sugar together. Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, flour and baking soda. Mix for 2 minutes with electric mixer. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: kiki's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the mixture, beating well. Stir in flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Start in a cold oven at 300°.
Cook approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan and then line it with wax paper and set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, brown sugar and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla and salt; mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread batter onto prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Loosen sides of cake.
Invert onto a plate.
Peel off wax paper.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda into a bowl. Mix to a loose dough with the well soured milk. Turn out on to a floured board and knead lightly until the underside is smooth. Turn the smooth side up. Place in a well heated, greased, 8-inch cast iron pot. Make a cross on top with a floured knife. Cover with lid. Bake in a 375-400 degree oven for about 40 minutes. Alternatively, a baking sheet may be used instead of an iron pot.

title: gingerbread loaf
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: children's delight
directions: Beat shortening and eggs together.
Add sugar and spices, then remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a greased angel cake pan or will make 36 cupcakes.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: edible play dough
directions: Knead ingredients together until dough is consistency with clay.
Place in sealed containers to keep dough from drying out.

title: cranberry crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Melt margarine in large pot and add flour to make a smooth paste.
Gradually add beef broth and water and cook until slightly thickened.
Saute ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add beef to large pot.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Cook butter, onions, bell pepper and flour until onions are done, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook for about
30 to 45 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter fingers(candy)
directions: Melt together the paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
(Use real chocolate chips for best results.)

title: artichoke balls
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil for 2 minutes.
Remove cloves; add mashed artichokes and eggs.
Simmer, stirring, for 5 minutes. Combine bread crumbs with remaining ingredients.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup bread crumb mixture (depending on how moist artichokes are) to artichoke mixture.
Form into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes, turning, until browned.
Serve hot.
Yields 25 to 30.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy apple crunch cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except chopped nuts in large mixing bowl with electric mixer on low speed until moistened.
Then beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: hot chip dip
directions: Empty cheese soup into top of a double boiler; add cheese pieces.
Heat over hot water until well blended.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Saute onions and pepper in a small amount of butter.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add all other ingredients. Keep warm over hot water until ready to serve.
Serve with taco chips.

title: corn cakes
directions: Preheat griddle to 375 degrees. Combine egg and milk. Add salt and corn meal; stir until smooth. Cook on slightly greased griddle until bubbles form and edges are dry. Turn and bake on other side. Keep batter stirred. Makes about 20 very thin corn cakes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix in bowl the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Pour onto cookie sheet that has been greased well and floured.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over cake and bake for 15 minutes at 350°, no more than 15 minutes

title: clam dip
directions: Sprinkle juice of clam and mix.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: penuche squares
directions: Melt butter.
Cool slightly; beat in brown sugar.
Add egg, flour and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Lightly stir in chocolate or butterscotch bits.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; do not overbake.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: molded gazpacho
directions: Soften gelatin in 1 cup cold tomato juice.
Bring to a boil. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased Bundt pan (ring mold is not large enough).
Refrigerate.
Unmold to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: new corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart ovenproof casserole with a nonstick vegetable coating.
In a mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add the egg substitute, cream-style and whole kernel corn, sour cream, buttermilk and margarine.
Mix well and pour into prepared casserole.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: open face tacos(amounts to serve 40)
directions: Make
individual tacos by layering on each plate in the order listed.

title: sausage balls with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients. Brown in vegetable oil; drain well and set aside.
Simmer next 4 ingredients for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Mix together, knead and
let rise.
Roll out and cut in squares.
Let rise on
cookie
sheets.
Fry in hot Crisco oil. Cool and frost.
This makes about 6 dozen.

title: turkey salad
directions: Boil turkey legs until tender.
Let cool, then remove meat from the bones.
Chop meat in small pieces. Add in chopped celery and red pepper.
Mix in bowl the relish, mayonnaise and boiled eggs (chopped).
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Blend all ingredients together and serve over lettuce or on bread.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rhubarb over cake.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb. Pour the whipping cream over sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine in sprayed oblong casserole dish. Sprinkle with crackers and margarine. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix (dry), softened margarine and egg until crumbly; reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining crumbly mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until crust appears dry, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Heat margarine, milk and caramels over low heat, stirring occasionally until caramels are melted.
Pour over crust; sprinkle with nuts, reserved crumbly mixture and chocolate chips. Bake until crumbly mixture appears dry and begins to brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Loosen edges of bars with spatula; refrigerate until caramel mixture becomes firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Drain cherries well; cut into halves, if cherries are large.
Toss cherries in flour mixture to coat.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Beat until creamy, then add butter and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into greased large dish.
Chill and cut into squares.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place whole heads of garlic in a small baking dish and bake them at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine the instant pudding and milk, then add the Cool Whip; stir.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan with graham crackers. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top and add another layer of graham crackers.
Pour on the rest of the pudding. Finish with a layer of grahams on top.
Add 3 tablespoons milk to the chocolate frosting and stir together.
Spread icing on top of the layer of graham crackers. Cover and chill at least 12 hours before serving.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in 9 x 13-inch pan, greasing sides also. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over butter in pan.
Place frozen rolls on top.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Dot with the 1/4 cup butter.
Place in cold oven, uncovered, overnight.
Next morning turn oven to 300° and bake 25 minutes.

title: peanut jumble cookies
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, margarine and peanut butter together and boil for 1 minute.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: eggplant caponata
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Chop onion, peppers and garlic. Drain mushrooms.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for about 1/2 hour.
Stir frequently.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: microwave spanish rice
directions: Place beef in 3-quart microproof casserole; break up with fork.
Stir in onion.
Cook on High 7 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Cover and cook on High 12 to 14 minutes, or until rice is tender, stirring once during cooking time.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Mix sweet potatoes and eggs; add margarine and milk and beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add allspice and salt; mix 1 minute at medium speed.
Add walnuts and mix 1/2 minute at medium speed or until well blended.
Drop by tablespoons into preheated 365° deep fat fryer; fry 3 minutes, turning several times until fritters are golden brown.
Remove from fat with slotted spoon and drain on a paper towel.
Serve hot.
Fritters can be kept hot for a short time in a warm oven until the whole batch is ready.

title: caramels
directions: Cook sugar and syrup to 245°, then start adding cream and butter slowly.
Cook on high.
Do not lose boil.
Turn heat to medium and cook to 242° or 243° (soft ball but firm).
Pour into large buttered cooking sheet.
Cool, cut and wrap.

title: curried fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix butter, brown sugar and curry powder. Lay fruit in a shallow baking dish, hollow side up.
Dot all over with butter and sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Cool and refrigerate for at least one day.
Warm over at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 10.
Must be made a day ahead.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, celery, garlic and bell peppers.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add water and crawfish tails.
Salt and pepper. Simmer until tails are tender.
Add green onions and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind pickles, onions, green peppers and red pepper up.
Add coarse salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain off all liquid.
Add mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, black pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Pour sauce over raw chicken (enough sauce for 1 fryer).
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry whip pie
directions: Slice
or cut strawberries into quarters.
Save several perfect
berries for garnish if desired.
Just before serving, whip the
cream
in a chilled bowl with a chilled beater until stiff; add	lemon
juice, then beat in the sugar.
Fold in the strawberries
lightly
and	turn into the pie shell.
Top with the selected whole berries.
Serve at once.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add this mixture a little at a time alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in oven at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: seafood alfredo pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut all vegetables in small strips. Saute vegetables until blanched (softer but crisp).
Season vegetables with Italian seasoning; salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Saute until shrimp are pink; remove from heat.
Prepare pizza dough as directed on package.
Spread out on pan.
Baste dough with garlic and margarine.
Bake dough for 2 minutes; remove from oven and spread Alfredo sauce over crust.
Place sauteed veggies and seafood over top evenly.
Sprinkle with 3 cheeses and bake for 10 minutes, then cool for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar together.
Then mix the Cool Whip and strawberries.
Pour over the chilled graham cracker crust.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Hollow out 1 loaf of bread and place dip in center.
Use bread for dipping.

title: eggplant stew
directions: Add all the above ingredients into a large pot and cook until the eggplant is tender and a fork goes through it easily.
You can either add pasta to the stew or serve it over pasta when it is done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in butter.
Add onions, mushrooms and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Five minutes before serving, add 1 pint of sour cream.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, syrup, salt and cream of tartar hard for 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Mix well.
Work quickly.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread out on cookie sheets.
Bake for 1 hour at 200° in buttered cookie sheets.
Stir occasionally.

title: long island iced tea
directions: Blend in mixer all but Pepsi or Coke.
Pour over ice into tall glass 3/4 of the way up; fill rest with pop and stir.
If too strong, add more sour mix.

title: aunt sue's spinach dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream with a mixer.
Blend well and add mayonnaise, soup mix and garlic.
Stir in spinach. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables (carrots, broccoli, celery, radishes, cukes, etc.) or Doritos type of chip.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1 cup of sugar in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Pinch holes in top and glaze (juice of one lemon and 3/4 cup powdered sugar glaze) while hot.
Cool before removing from pan.
Grate lemon peel into batter for stronger lemon taste.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on each layer.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool layers, coconut side up.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and chop into 1/2-inch squares.
Peel onion and chop.
Put both in large boiler.
Add 2 quarts of water.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add margarine, milk, salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter bar dessert
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and frost over top.

title: cornmeal mini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 3 mini muffin pans with butter, margarine or nonstick spray.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir to blend.
Make a well in the center; set aside.

title: stuffed eggs and beef rolls
directions: Combine eggs, corned beef, pickle relish, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Lightly brush inside of each roll with butter. Fill with egg filling.
Replace top. Wrap in foil. Refrigerate. Can be served cold or bake wrapped at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: lemon zucchini bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer combine applesauce, apple juice, fructose, oil, eggs and lemon juice.
Beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl combine lemon peel, flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add zucchini and nuts to dry mixture.
Add batter to dry mixture and blend well. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan which has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: swedish meatballs(reduced-fat recipe)
directions: Add bread to milk.
Mix in next 6 ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in electric frying pan.
tags: Healthy Choice extra lean ground beef

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool.
Add onion and green peppers.
Combine and add remaining ingredients. Stir several times while marinating.
Serve cold.
Can be kept in refrigerator several weeks.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix soups, Cheez Whiz and onion flakes.
Pour over vegetables and top with dried French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until browned.
Drain.
Add sugar and barbecue sauce.
Mix well, then remove from heat.
Shape biscuits into cupcake muffin pan.
(Spray pan with Pam.)
Spoon meat mixture into biscuits.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: never fail whole wheat pie crust
directions: Combine flours, shortening and salt (mix flours well).
Cut in shortening.
Whip together vinegar, egg and water and add to dry ingredients; mix well.
(Can't overhandle.) Makes enough dough for 2 large two crust pies.

title: carrots a l'orange
directions: Add carrots and onion to boiling salted water.
Cover and boil gently until carrots are tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain; save 2 tablespoons liquid.
Add orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and cooking liquid saved from boiling carrots to drained carrots.
Stir gently.
Reheat to serving temperature.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg in a mixing bowl; combine the milk, egg and margarine.
Add orange juice, rind, chopped apples and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; stir into milk mixture with a spoon until well blended.
Do Not overmix.
Preheat oil to 350°.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown, turning so they brown evenly.
Serve with apple butter.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients, then toss with dressing.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except crushed potato chips. Put into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Cover with crushed potato chips. Bake for one hour at 370 degrees.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes and 1/2 cup of the cheese and 1/2 cup of French fried onion rings.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes, uncovered.

title: strawberry dessert salad
directions: Make the jello using 1 cup water and 1 cup strawberry juice. Allow to come to room temperature and place in blender with 2 cups sliced strawberries and one small (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip. Blend mixture.
Place in large bowl or glass baking dish or jello mold and refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter; add onions and cook 30 minutes or until golden on medium.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Preheat broiler. Pour soup in 6 ovenproof bowls.
Place on baking sheet.
Add 2 tablespoons shredded cheese, 2 slices bread and 2 slices cheese to each bowl.
Place under broiler for 3 minutes or until cheese is golden and bubbly.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and pour 1/2 into mold. Refrigerate until solid.
(Leave other half out of refrigerator.) When mixture is solid, cover with 1/2 pint of sour cream.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: bird in a bag
directions: Thaw
turkey completely.
Remove inside packages.
Cook neck in 4 cups of water to make stock; set aside for gravy and dressing.
Rinse turkey, pat dry with paper towel.	Grease the inside
of	paper bag with shortening and place turkey inside. Roll
up
end
and	place
in
roasting
pan,
breast side up. Preheat oven
to
and bake on lower rack for about 2 1/2 hours.
Turkey
cooks much faster using this method and browns well.
Cut	away
brown
bag
carefully.
Cool for at least 20 minutes before carving.

title: tossed waldorf salad
directions: Core apples and slice or dice.
Toss with lemon juice.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Serve in
large lettuce-lined bowl or in individual lettuce-lined plate.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Place apples in lightly greased 9-inch round cake pan. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup walnuts; sprinkle over apples.
Sift together the flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Pour over apple mixture.
Top with nuts. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beer and cheddar fondue
directions: Cook ground pork sausage in a large saucepan over medium heat, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink.
Drain and remove sausage from pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat; add onion and garlic, and saute until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sausage, beer, and next 3 ingredients.
Transfer to a fondue pot or slow cooker; keep warm on LOW.
Serve with cubed French bread or sliced pears. Makes about 6 cups.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: On medium heat, place oil and flour in black skillet and stir until brown.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Reduce heat. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, parsley, green onions, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add cooked rice and mix well.
Place lid on pot until ready to serve.
Serves about 6.

title: toasted soy beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in salt water.
Boil 1 hour in same water.
Drain beans.
Spread beans in shallow pan.
Roast at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
"They make great snacks."

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and add milk and salt.
Cook slowly until thick.
Onion or parsley may be added to sauce.
Put sauce into casserole.
Alternate with potatoes, cheese and hard-boiled eggs.
Put 1/2 of bread crumbs and cheese on top. Bake until brown (30 minutes to 1 hour).

title: economy casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, celery and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread 2/3 can (large) Chinese noodles on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together and put in greased muffin tins.
Bake in 425° oven until light brown on top.
Makes 12.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in small bowl.
Set aside.

title: lemon flake jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: sausage-noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet and drain.
Remove sausage to drain on paper towel lined plate.
Pour all but a small amount of grease from skillet and saute onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, meat and spices.
Simmer sauce for 15 to 20 minutes while cooking egg noodles.
Drain noodles; return to pot and stir in sour cream.
Pour half of sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add noodles and rest of sauce.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie chicken broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook chicken and onion quickly in hot margarine until just done.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice, thyme, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; cook covered 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook covered 3 to 4 minutes.

title: auntie bev's chicken-mushroom casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a buttered or Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch casserole with the raw boneless chicken.
Next place sliced cheese to cover chicken.
Add a layer of mushrooms, then spread the soup over all.
Cover with a layer of the stuffing or bread crumbs, as thick as you like.
Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine or butter over crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven, then uncover and cook for a remaining 15 minutes.

title: copper pennies(or marinated carrots)
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper in slices and mix with cooked carrots.
