Mix remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables; cover and marinate at least 12 hours or longer.
Drain to serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator indefinitely.
When all vegetables have been used, put another batch in, after simmering sauce down to original thickness.
Yields 2 pints.

title: chicken and shrimp gumbo
directions: Stew chicken in about a gallon of water (reserve stock for gumbo); remove from bones.
Cook okra (if frozen or fresh), onions, bell pepper and tomatoes in oil slowly for about 30 minutes.
Make a roux with 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons oil.
Add roux, vegetables and chicken to hot chicken broth.
Add other seasonings and cook slowly for about
2 hours.
(If using canned okra, add to gumbo after about an hour.)
Add shrimp and cook until done.
To serve, add fresh onion tops and parsley and serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Peel.
Fry onion and bacon together until nearly crisp.
Cube or slice potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and water together; cook until sugar is dissolved. Add cut potatoes to sugar and water dressing.
Fold gently and serve.
Serves 10.

title: mom's overnight cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Form in dollar size rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice then bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces.
Mix hot dogs and ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Great for parties!

title: caesar salad
directions: Clean lettuce and chill.
Crush up garlic cloves and add all remaining ingredients except croutons.
When ready to serve, break up the romaine lettuce.
Pour mixture over lettuce and add croutons and pepper to taste.

title: thelma's overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly into pan. Place frozen rolls in pan (4 per row).
Sprinkle pudding mix on top of rolls.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Put a wet towel over pan and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Mix together broccoli, cheese and onion.
Put into pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread and place in a greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, salt and cooking oil, then add 4 to 5 tablespoons cold water.
Makes 2 crust pie.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the ingredients in order.
Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: butterscotch or chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour and butter with pastry blender.
Spread into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with pecans and press into flour mixture.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: white clam sauce with linguini
directions: Warm oil in saucepan with butter.
Add the basil, red and black pepper, garlic and cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Add clams and juice. Bring to a second boil.
Pour over linguini.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat chicken piccata
directions: Mix together flour and pepper; dredge chicken lightly in seasoned flour, shaking off excess.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a skillet and saute chicken 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until golden.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add 1/2 of the stock and lemon juice to skillet, bring to a boil, and boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet and place 1 lemon slice on each cutlet.
Cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon and place on a heated serving platter; reserve pan liquid.
Surround chicken with cooked lemon slices.
Add remaining 1/4 cup stock to pan liquid and cook over medium-high heat until reduced to a thin syrupy glaze.
Remove from heat and blend in remaining 1 tablespoon margarine, stirring until margarine melts.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients for 1 minute.
Take off stove. Add peanut butter.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Cool.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Slowly add sugar which has been mixed with cornstarch and salt.
Beat until thick.
Scald milk until scum forms.
Slowly add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla. Cook in bowl or 1-quart measuring cup until thick and bubbly (High 3 to 4 minutes).
Stir once or twice.
Cool.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute onion and pepper in butter or margarine for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli; mix well.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup to mixture.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add garlic salt; mix well.
Pour into prepared rice; stir mixture until well blended. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Will make ten 1-cup servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat
Crisco
and sugar until smooth.
Alternate adding beaten eggs, vanilla and applesauce with flour, soda, salt and baking soda.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Serves 12 people.

title: christmas candy
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and cream until it makes a soft ball in cold water.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over cooled brownies.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips in microwave. Stir in cereal.
Spread over Marshmallow Creme layer.
Chill before cutting and store in refrigerator.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup chow mein noodles, tuna, celery and cashews.
Toss lightly.
Place in a baking dish. Sprinkle 1 cup chow mein noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peach crumble
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar.
Mix until creamy. Fold in pecans.
Spread mixture on a slightly greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from sheet onto waxed paper and allow to cool.
Mix milk and pudding mix until thick.
Stir in sour cream.

title: hominy chili supper
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion in shortening until it is browned and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain fat.
Add this mixture and other ingredients to large saucepan and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with chips or cornbread.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions.
Make 4 thin layers or split 2 layers to make 4 layers.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Place rolls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle pudding on top of rolls.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon over rolls. Cover with cloth and let rise overnight.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Flip over while hot.

title: red party punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add enough water to make 2 gallons.
For green punch, substitute 2 packages lemon-lime Kool-Aid for strawberry Kool-Aid and cranberry sauce.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: perky punch
directions: Pour 7-Up and juices into 10-cup percolator.
Put spices in percolator basket.
Start percolator and perk about 10 minutes. Remove basket.
Serve hot.
Makes 7 (6-ounce) cups.

title: turkey and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, saute chopped onions in 4 tablespoons of the butter until the onions are soft.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and liquid, light cream and sherry.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add turkey, ham and water chestnuts.
Transfer to a shallow 2-quart baking dish or casserole.
Top with cheese.
Melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter, mix with bread crumbs and sprinkle around the edge of the casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes until hot and light brown.

title: duck soup
directions: Put duck in large soup pot; cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and skim.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours with prunes, cloves, allspice, bay leaf, marjoram and salt.
When duck is tender, add blood.
Thicken soup with flour; flavor with sugar and vinegar.
Serve with potato noodles.

title: turtles
directions: Mix sugar, butter, evaporated milk and vanilla together and boil for 7 minutes.
Mix together marshmallow cream, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into the sugar mixture.
Beat for a few minutes, then drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and flavor packets from Ramen noodles. Add crushed noodles, broccoli slaw, almonds and sunflower seeds. Let marinate for 30 minutes before serving. Great served with hamburgers or fish.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix ingredients
together.
May
have to add more flour as needed to roll out	and
cut
(about 2 to 3 cups).	Bake at 375° for 10
to	12
minutes.
Make icing with powdered sugar, butter, vanilla and hot water;
spread on cookies.

title: golden mushroom chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg and coat with flour.
Pan-fry the chops until brown.
Combine soup and 2 cans of water.
Place chops in large 2-quart (covered) casserole dish; pour soup mixture over chops.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours, covered.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: hershey's milk chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate bar, butter/margarine and boiling water in medium mixing bowl; stir until chocolate is melted.
Combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt in large mixer bowl. Gradually add chocolate mixture, beating until thoroughly blended. Blend in eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool completely.
Frost as desired.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower flowerets (5 minutes). In bowl, add crushed tomatoes and shredded cheese. Put in 9 x 13 dish and add crushed crackers with melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: special english toffee
directions: Butter 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, water and almonds.
Cook over high heat until mixture becomes caramel colored and candy thermometer reaches 235° (7 to 10 minutes).
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and spread chocolate as it melts.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Let stand in cool place until chocolate hardens.
Break into small pieces, about 2 pounds.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Form dough into balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: contemporary resort's french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt well (do not beat) in a flat pan.
Dip bread into mixture, being sure slices are well covered.
Heat shortening or margarine in skillet and fry bread to a golden brown.
Dip in sugar and serve with maple syrup.

title: taco pie
directions: Make a crust with flour, mayonnaise and enough milk to moisten. Brown ground beef. Add taco mix with 1/2 cup water. Add onion, pepper and tomato to crust. Add ground beef mixture. Frost with a mixture of mayonnaise, sour cream and cheese. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in mixture.
Top with 4 ounces shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut off top 1/4.
Scoop out seeds and pulp. Turn upside down to drain.
Cook spinach.
Drain well; squeeze dry.
Place cooked spinach in a saucepan.
Mix sour cream with flour, Parmesan cheese and salad dressing.
Add to spinach.
Cook mixture over medium heat until thickened.
Place tomato shells in casserole dish, using sides to help support them.
Fill shells with spinach stuffing.
Top with bread crumbs sauteed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pan-glazed chicken with basil
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chicken with salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Add chicken; cook 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Turn chicken and cook 6 minutes or until chicken is done. Stir in vinegar, honey and basil; cook an additional 1 minute. Makes 4 servings. Since this recipe is tasty, quick, easy, low fat and uses few ingredients, I find I use it again and again.

title: mushroom and barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in pot.
Cook slowly 3 or 4 hours or until thick.
If soup should thicken too much while standing, add water.
Stir frequently.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat
chocolate
and
2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream
cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and
beat until
smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping, blending
until
smooth.
Spoon
into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all
together well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Add oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir all together and drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Allow to harden.
They should be ready in about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy venison roast
directions: Combine vinegar and 2 quarts water.
Add roast.
Soak overnight.
Rinse well.
Soak in salted water for 2 hours.
Rinse. Combine 1 teaspoon salt, lemon pepper marinade, oregano and seasoned salt.
Rub on roast.
Cover with garlic and onion.
Place in a slow cooker.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup water.
Cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.

title: orange pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, spices, salt and orange rind.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 40 minutes longer.
Cool. To serve, top with whipped topping and garnish with orange half slices, if desired.

title: monkey bread
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon. Grease a Bundt pan with 2 tablespoons melted butter. "Flour" pan with 4 tablespoons of the sugar and cinnamon mixture. Take each biscuit, dip in melted butter, then dip in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Stack biscuits in pan. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in preheated 400° oven. Allow to stand for 5 minutes, then take out of pan.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: In saucepan combine spinach and onion; cook according to spinach package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
Combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, butter or margarine, and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Cover and chill till serving time. (Or place in a freezer container; seal, label, and freeze.)
To serve, place chilled or frozen puffs on a baking sheet.	Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.	Bake chilled puffs for 10 to 12 minutes; bake frozen puffs for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 60.
The taste of these top-rated tidbits is similar to spinach dumplings.

title: lemon marinated chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a glass dish.
Add chicken breasts.
Turn to coat with marinade.
Marinate about 2 hours. Broil or grill 4 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes per side or until thoroughly cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot olive cheese balls
directions: Cut biscuits in two sections.
Wrap each piece around an olive and roll in cheese. Bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: leta hall's spinach jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water, then add ginger ale or lemon soda. Cool.
Mix. Let set overnight in 1-quart dish. Serves 8 or 9.

title: old fashion potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until almost soft.
Hard boil eggs.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Pare potatoes and cut into medium size pieces. Add ten chopped boiled eggs.
Add diced up celery, onion and olives.
Mix together.
In separate bowl, add Miracle Whip, milk, vinegar, mustard, black pepper, parsley flakes, garlic salt and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over potato mixture and stir until evenly coated.
Garnish top with 2 leftover sliced boiled eggs.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Rinse broccoli under running water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese and the onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand blender.

Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes. Top with remaining cheese. Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer. Garnish with tomato slices, if desired.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onion, celery and green peppers. Add to beef.
Add next 4 ingredients, mixing well; heat thoroughly.
Top with Chinese noodles.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes.
Add first margarine, sour cream, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Grate cheese and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake until
melted, about 10 minutes at 450°.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over first ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: swans island lobster dip
directions: Blend small amount of mayonnaise into cream cheese and continue adding all of the mayonnaise until smooth and well blended. Add remaining ingredients and serve in bowl or crock with crackers or chips.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

Cream the butter, oil and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder. Add flour mixture alternately with milk to cream mixture. Add vanilla; blend well. Turn into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: best you've ever eaten cheesecake
directions: Mix with spoon.
Spoon carefully over cheese mixture and bake again at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours and then refrigerate.
This cheesecake takes a little more effort than most, but once you try it nothing else will do.

title: peachy punch
directions: Thaw 1 package of peaches.
Mix thawed peaches, lemon juice and fruit punch.
Pour over frozen peaches in a chilled punch bowl.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole on top or raw rice.
Top each with slice of onion, bell pepper and tomato.
Season with salt, pepper and dash of curry powder.
Rinse skillet (used to brown meat) with 2 cups boiling water or a can of bouillon and 1/2 cup water.
Pour into casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
(I like to add a little curry powder to rice.)

title: chicken and homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs in bowl with fork. Add salt and beat again. Stir in 1 cup flour and beat smooth with fork. Continue adding flour, one cup at a time, until dough is stiff.
Turn out on floured surface and roll out very thin.
Make sure to have plenty of flour underneath so dough won't stick.

title: peggy's lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, baking powder, extract, raisins, and nuts.
Line pan, bundt or angel food pan, with waxed paper or shortening/flour.
Cook for 3 hours at 275°.

title: coffee can raisin bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with yeast.
Stir water, milk, oleo, sugar and salt over low heat until oleo melts.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add yeast and flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining flour, eggs, and raisins.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Coat inside of 2 (1 pound) coffee cans with small amount of oil. Divide dough in half.
Put in cans and put lids on.
Let rise until 1-inch from top of cans.
Remove lids and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until top sounds hollow when tapped.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in microwave; bring to boil, 3 to 4 minutes.
When sugar mixture comes to a boil, take out and add the soda.
Pour over the popped corn in brown paper bag.
Put back in microwave for 60 seconds.
Take out and shake; put in microwave for 60 seconds.

title: graham cracker jello dessert
directions: *Drain pineapple; use juice as part of liquid to make Jell-O.

title: fish with pecan butter sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, place equal amounts of oil and butter enough to cover the bottom of the pan.
Season the fish in the Creole seasoning.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and turn into a greased baking dish.

title: corn and chicken chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute
the
vegetables
until tender.
Add the flour and stir
into
a paste.
Add the stock and cream.
Simmer 20 minutes.	Add
chicken and simmer 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.	Yields 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy by hand (not mixer).
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder sifted together.
Add 1 cup nuts (optional).
Mix until blended.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; decrease temperature to 325° and bake for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix the ingredients in a saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook until thick.

title: "soused wild ducks"
directions: Season ducks liberally, inside and out, with Morton Season-All. Brown in oil.
Drain excess oil.
Add wine.
Bake, covered, breast sides down, one hour at 350°.
Turn breast side up.
Add drained mushrooms.
Re-cover and continue baking until tender.
When done, remove duck from sauce.
Add cream of mushroom soup and blend well. Bone duck and return to sauce.

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir until blended.
Stir in butter, coconut and pineapple. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set, covering with aluminum foil after 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Sprinkle salt over top and beat until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, then flavoring.
Fold in coconut and corn flakes.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (or until done).
One-half hour before done, spread some ketchup on top of meat loaf.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, salt, shortening and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, sour milk, flour and cocoa.
Beat for another 2 minutes.
Then add the boiling water, in which is dissolved the baking soda.
Beat for 1 minute.
Turn into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until beef is lightly browned.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Turn into an 8-inch square pan or 1 1/4-quart casserole dish.
Cut cheese into thin strips and place over beef mixture.
Cut biscuits into bite size pieces and place over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans well. Shape into ball.
Roll in crushed pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: amazing pie
directions: Add the first 5 ingredients together and beat well in blender. Add coconut, eggs, 1 at a time.
Pour into a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, mix well.
Add liquids.
Hand mix until thoroughly combined.
Can store in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Spoon out of container onto greased muffin cups.
Do not stir mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken-pineapple skillet
directions: Cut each breast half into 10 to 12 strips.
Combine in bowl the pineapple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and soy sauce.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Crumble 1 box of 2 layer cake mix (yellow, white or spice) over pumpkin mixture.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef supreme
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Cook noodles according to package. Drain noodles, then stir in butter.
Blend together sour cream, soup and seasoning.
Alternate layers of noodles, beef mixture, cheese and soup mixture in greased 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in water to cover for 2 hours or until soft. If there is excess water, reserve 1/2 cup.
Roughly chop the apricots and set aside.
(Chopping the apricots first, then soaking them is easier.)
Using a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; sift 3 times.
This is to mix all the dry ingredients evenly.
Stir in the nuts and set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and place in baking dish.

title: golden crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until smooth. Scrape dough from side of bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into 12-inch circle.
Spread with butter.
Cut into 16 wedges.
Roll up each wedge, beginning at rounded edge.
Place rolls with point under.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg and add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tortellini-vegetable kabobs
directions: Cook tortellini, drain and set aside.
Combine cornstarch and next 7 ingredients in small saucepan, gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil, cook 30 seconds stirring with wire whisk.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: elfin magic
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sandtortchen (sand tarts)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Gradually blend in the flour.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll as thin as possible on well-floured board.
Work with 1/4 of the dough at a time.
Keep remaining dough chilled.
Cut into diamonds with a knife.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Brush each cookie with beaten egg white. Sprinkle with sugar and a pinch of cinnamon.
Place a pecan half in center of each cookie.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool on cookie sheets 1 minute, then remove to wire racks.
Store in airtight tins.
Yields 24 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together and let sit overnight.

title: sweetheart fudge pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, coffee powder and rum extract, mixing well.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Pour mixture into prepared 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes; cool completely on a wire rack. Chill.
Before serving, pipe whipped cream on top of the pie.
Garnish with cherries.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; add egg yolks one at a time. Blend after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan (be sure to use a large deep pan or it will overflow).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: frosted pate
directions: Mash liverwurst.
Blend in onion and 1/4 cup mayonnaise. Mound into desired shape.
(Line bowl with plastic wrap.) Chill.

title: bell pepper jelly
directions: Combine all the ingredients except pectin in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add pectin and pour at once into sterilized jelly jars and seal.

title: stuffed cabbage(moosewood cookbook)
directions: Parboil the cabbage in water, 10 to 15 minutes, or until outer leaves are easily removable.
Remove the first 12 leaves.
Make sure the cabbage is cooked well enough so leaves will not break when rolled.
Saute vegetable (not apple), nuts and seeds in butter until onion is transparent and nuts roasted.
Combine the saute with remaining ingredients and season to taste.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix the chocolate chips, 2 tablespoons sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes.
Place remaining ingredients into a medium saucepan.
Mix water with flour first, then seasonings.
As sauce begins to thicken, add milk so it won't turn lumpy.
Place cooked potatoes in casserole dish and pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Simmer together with meat sauce for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dice chicken breasts into small squares.
Bring soup and sour cream to a bubble.
Add olives.
Fill tortillas with chicken pieces and soup mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Top with remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 25 minutes. Uncover.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: peanut butter cracker bars
directions: Crumble crackers.
Bring to boil the sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, crackers and vanilla.
Pour into a greased dish and let cool, then cut into squares.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 cup pineapple juice instead of water and mix as directed on box.
Cook in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese, pudding mix and milk, then fold in drained pineapple and spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over that and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Let stand in refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight.

title: garlic dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Serve with rippled potato chips or corn chips.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° until firm and golden brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and stuffing.
Salt chicken with seasoned salt.
Dip chicken in Italian dressing and roll in cheese mixture.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. In a saucepan, mix broth and soup and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
In another bowl, combine pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Add melted margarine and mix thoroughly.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Butter and shortening can be used half and half.
Roll on floured surface into desired thickness, then cut with small cutter. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This is a soft cookie that keeps well.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Finish filling ice cream can with milk.
That's it!
Prepare ice cream as usual for homemade ice cream.
Delicious!

title: favorite baked chicken
directions: Place foil inside baking dish.
Place meat on large piece of foil.
Pour on rest of ingredients.
Close tightly.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until chicken is tender.
Gravy is in foil when opened.
Serves 6.

title: cherry tomatoes filled with cheese
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut in halves and with a teaspoon, take out the insides and let drain.
Brown the beef and cut into tiny little pieces.
Mix with cream cheese, Parmesan, sour cream and garlic powder, then fill up the tomatoes with this mixture.
Brown the onions and mushrooms then mix in paprika and salt and spread on top of the stuffed tomatoes.
Serve as appetizers.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add milk, butter and cheese mixture.
Stir in frankfurters and onions.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour into buttered baking dish.
Add 2 slices of cheese on top of macaroni.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with buttered Kix cereal.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bismarks
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 420° oven.
Blend eggs and milk in a blender.
Add flour to mixture in blender.
Pour mixture into hot pan and return to the oven for 12 minutes.
Serve hot with apricot jam.
Dust with powdered sugar and lemon juice.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring oil, vinegar, sugar and salt to a rolling boil. Pour slowly over slaw, onion and pepper.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours without stirring.
Store in plastic container.
Will keep in refrigerator for a month.

title: 24 hour pickles
directions: Will need 2 quart jars.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter in a large skillet.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add milk, cream cheese, hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until mixed thoroughly.
Cook green beans for 15 to 20 minutes and drain.
Add water chestnuts and almonds.
Pour sauce over green beans in a casserole or crock-pot.
Cook until hot.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a deep, large pot, mix the salt, margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Cook 5 minutes on medium to medium-high.
Remove from heat and mix in baking soda.
Mixture will "puff" up and turn lighter in color.
Pour this over the popped corn.
I use 2 large disposable/reusable aluminum foil roasting pans.
Mix well; will mix better when warm.
Place pans in 250° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Stir around several times during baking time to mix caramel with corn.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store tightly covered.
